(28, 'India', 'Lakshadweep', NULL, 'lakshadweep', '', '', NULL, '1587549398_5ea014d664be7.jpeg', NULL, '1587549398_5ea014d66695f.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>Lakshadweep is a wonderful tropical archipelago of 36 atolls and coral reefs in the Laccadive Sea, off the coast of Kerala, India. Not all of the islands are inhabited, and only a few are open to visitors. Lakshadweep is also known as the coral islands as they were formed from the corals. The islands are&nbsp;famous&nbsp;for their rich marine life due to the stable temperatures of the waters.&nbsp;Lakshadweep&nbsp;islands are a&nbsp;famous&nbsp;beach destination of India with crystal clear blue waters and coral reefs. The islands are also known for pearl fishing and are a major supplier of sea- food.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Food</h4><p>The cuisine of Lakshadweep has a whole range of the freshest seafood mixed with a generous use of coconut. The food ranges from spicy non-veg to healthy veg and most often a certain authentic Kerala-element is obvious in the cuisine. Besides the vegetables and seafood, local people are also very fond of rice. Tuna fish being the most abundant, there are many varieties of dishes like grilled or baked tuna fish, rayereha (red tuna curry) and sannath (white coconut-based tuna). It is also known for the dishes like white coconut roti and Malabar parotta.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Culture</h4><p>Lakshadweep is culturally vibrant and diverse. The majority of population being Muslim, the culture here is heavily influenced by Islamic culture. Cultures of neighboring states like Kerala can also be seen here. Parichakali dance, kolkali dance and lava dance are the popular dance forms performed during weddings and festivals. Corals are an important part of the culture as well. Intricately designed ornaments and jewelry made out of shells and corals are a prominent part of the art and craft tradition.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Agatti island</li><li>Bagaram atoll</li><li>Kadmat island</li><li>Kalpeni</li><li>Kilthan island</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d4019476.361155808!2d70.54012096308199!3d10.320273093314078!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3b9fcd65cae4973d%3A0x17bd7416842ce9aa!2sLakshadweep!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587550597045!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-22 20:56:38', '2020-04-22 20:56:38'),
(29, 'India', 'Arunachal Pradesh', NULL, 'arunachal-pradesh', '', '', NULL, '1587549703_5ea0160763c8a.jpeg', NULL, '1587549703_5ea0160765afc.jpeg', NULL, '<h2>About</h2><p>Arunachal Pradesh or the land of dawn lit mountains, as its name suggests, is a northeastern state, which shares its borders with Assam and Nagaland. The largest of the northeastern states, Arunachal Pradesh is reverently known as the Land of the Rising Sun. It is a destination, which offers numerous cathartic experiences. If one is looking for the perfect summer getaway in a place which is peaceful and assures bare minimum interaction, or if one simply wishes to indulge in some self-recreation, they can get out of their the perfect vacation does not exi- phase and book a ticket to Arunachal Pradesh. We are sure your postcards or journal entry would end with and then there were no regrets.</p><h2>Food</h2><p>The standout point about the food of Arunachal Pradesh is the variety that it consists of. Numerous tribes have evolved over time in this place making it a diversity hub, which has resulted in the contrasting cuisine greatly. Overall, fried food is avoided by the natives and hence most of the dishes are either boiled or smoked. Food in eastern Arunachal Pradesh mostly comprises of bamboo and leafy vegetables. The places, which are closer to the border (Tibet), including Taiwan, have food items, which are rich in dairy products. The abundance of variety in the cuisine of this place assures that there is something for everyone here. The lack of fried food offers healthier yet scrumptious options for all the food lovers. Be it a vegetarian or a non-vegetarian, Arunachal delicacies are a delight for anyone who likes to experiment with their taste buds!&nbsp;</p><h2>Culture</h2><p>Being the hometown for 26 major tribes, Arunachal Pradesh is what one can literally term as the hub of diversity. The native languages of the people here are mostly derived from Tibeto-Burman language, which is further modified by over fifty dialects among various tribes. Assamese, Hindi and English are more prominently spoken besides the specific languages of the tribe due to the extended influence of Ahom dynasty. The culture and traditions, both religious and non-religious, are strongly influenced by nature in Arunachal Pradesh. From worshiping the sun and moon as deities to developing crafts and tools, which are prominently inclined towards nature, everything here depicts a deep-rooted sense of earthliness among the tribes. Hence for the people who appreciate down to earth traditions, which bring one closer to mother earth, Arunachal Pradesh is a must explore for them.&nbsp;</p><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Tawang</li><li>Namdapha National Park</li><li>Upper Dibang Valley</li><li>Ziro Valley</li><li>Tezu</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d7218461.860125015!2d89.98483169024078!3d27.943692433536764!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x374043466a1c7227%3A0x76b56e552f9a92f2!2sArunachal%20Pradesh!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587550883983!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-22 21:01:43', '2020-10-03 12:55:08'),
(30, 'India', 'Manipur', NULL, 'manipur', '', '', NULL, '1587962027_5ea660ab5b723.jpeg', NULL, '1587962027_5ea660ab5f500.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>Manipur is a place, which is greatly underrated, with a deep history, which largely remains unexplored by the majority of travelers. It resides between Nagaland, Mizoram and Assam, with Myanmar in the east. It has served as a connection between the Indian subcontinent and Central as well as Southeast Asia. Thus the culture in Manipur is greatly influenced by both. A trip to Manipur should be in the cards of every person who wishes to discover traditions and cultures, which remain obscure in mainland India. The best thing about this vacation destination is that it has to offer something for everyone. From a wildlife enthusiast to a historian, from a scenery lover to a culture explorer, Manipur has it all.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>Manipuri cuisine is probably one the healthiest option when it comes to food choices in India. The dishes are usually very simple to prepare and have a unique savory flavor to them because of the different spices used. The ingredients used in authentic Manipur food, by the native households, are purely organic and hence the taste is usually hard to replicate elsewhere. Even though the food offers a fair variety, most of the dishes are fish based. So if you wish to experience this particularly spicy, less oily and organic cuisine, a trip to Manipur is a must!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>Manipur offers one of the most amazing experiences when it comes to art, craft and culture. Dating back to a pre Christian era, the history of the native people is vast and full of reformations. Although Manipur is known for its firm religious beliefs and superstitions, the stories and folklore depicting these are numerous. Other than religion, craft and history, Manipur also has several dance forms which have garnered praise over time. With its simplicity and uniqueness, Manipuri culture has subtly wormed its way into the hearts of many. For those who love to uncover historical facts and thoroughly explore their origins, Manipur is surely a gold mine.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Leimaram Waterfalls</li><li>Chandel</li><li>Andro</li><li>Kakching</li><li>Dzukou Valley</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1854996.9268499466!2d92.73587851636863!3d24.75978771519805!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3749265bf16390db%3A0x8cc1691ae0a829af!2sManipur!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587963233868!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:33:47', '2020-04-27 15:33:47'),
(31, 'India', 'Meghalaya', NULL, 'meghalaya', '', '', NULL, '1587962218_5ea6616aab332.jpeg', NULL, '1587962218_5ea6616aadf01.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>The name of this state literally translates to the abode of clouds, which is true to the notch. This hill area seldom flaunts a cloudless sky, and is a go-to destination for people looking for a pleasant weather get away. The climate is neither too warm in the summers nor too cold in the winters and hence Meghalaya is a prompt vacation spot all year round. The state shares its borders at the south and west with Bangladesh and at the north and east with Assam. Meghalaya also presents us with one of the most diverse flora and fauna in the country. So when one wishes for a recreational vacation, Meghalaya ticks all the boxes!</p><h4>Food</h4><p>Rice and curry dishes are predominant in the Meghalayan cuisine. Rice is used to prepare delicacies ranging from sweets to fried rice, and not only that, but it is also used to prepare Kyat, a fermented rice beer. The flavor of Meghalayan food is not just by the spices. The traditional day to day dishes are prepared with generous amount of time, thus providing the food with deeply cooked flavours of all the ingredients present. This not only enhances the flavor but also gives the dishes a uniqueness of their own which is hard to replicate with quickly cooked food. Pork is another prominent ingredient, which is also a staple diet for most of the natives and is creatively used in many of the food items, be it occasional or regular dishes. Meghalaya thus serves as a must for food lovers as well as those who wish to try out a new cuisine!</p><h4>Culture</h4><p>Meghalaya is rich with tradition and culture and most famous for its dance and music. Various tribes residing in Meghalaya have their own dance forms and folklores which hold great historical value because of their ancient origins. Each form is unique and exclusively depicts the culture of its tribe. The art and craft of Meghalaya is a flourished sector which flaunts not only historical and religious roots of the state but also the modern traditions. Bamboo weaving is a highly sought after craft skill which also serves as the livelihood for many. If one wishes to learn about the lifestyle of tribesmen as well as connect with nature at its truest form, Meghalaya wouldnt disappoint.</p><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Nohkalikai Waterfalls</li><li>Double Decker Living Root Bridge</li><li>Umiam Lake</li><li>Elephant Falls</li><li>Dawki- Umngot River</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3685739.9741155915!2d89.0669595318715!3d25.559838740118472!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x37507e8f34bd207f%3A0xf5ef6117f496d6e!2sMeghalaya!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587963435120!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:36:58', '2020-04-27 15:36:58'),
(32, 'India', 'Mizoram', NULL, 'mizoram', '', '', NULL, '1587962469_5ea662651ce5d.jpeg', NULL, '1587962469_5ea662651f848.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>Mizoram, also known as the Land of Mizos, is the southernmost locked state out of the seven sisters and is surrounded by Assam, Tripura and Manipur. It also shares adjacent borders with Bangladesh and Myanmar. Like the other northeastern states, Mizoram too is abundantly inhabited by local tribal people. Since it has a lesser population, this state serves as an excellent getaway for those looking for a secluded vacation. The forested area also provides an intimacy with nature which is hard to get anywhere else. So if you wish to be surrounded by peace for a while, Mizoram is a definite go to destination.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>The cuisine of Mizoram is partly unique and partly shared with the other northeastern states. Rice, combined with various kinds of meat, like chicken, pork, beef, and fish, serve as the staple diet of the native people. Most of the dishes that one would encounter in Mizoram are garnished with meat products, thus providing Mizo cuisine with a different twist of flavor. Mizoram also boasts one of the healthiest cuisines in the country, due to less oil and inclusion of various vegetables. Trying out the healthy yet lip smacking Mizoram food should be on every wanderers to-eat list!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>The mizo people are said to be highly sociable and down to earth tribesmen. Their culture and traditions represent the same qualities for over numerous generations. The tradition of Mizo people greatly revolves around Jhuman cultivation, which depicts the roots they share with nature and their connection with agricultural practices from ancient times. The festivals of Mizoram are more social gatherings than religious ones and people from different walks of life can take part and enjoy these unique get-togethers indulgently. Music is another art which the Mizo people are passionate about. Various folk songs and tale songs, dating back decades, are still sung and danced upon by the people of Mizoram.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Aizawl</li><li>Vantawng Waterfalls</li><li>Dampa Tiger Reserve</li><li>Tamdil Lake</li><li>Phawngpui</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d1877203.205481014!2d91.7267276126245!3d23.228071427632518!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x374d0bd19f3f36f7%3A0xb1f62692a3d5e474!2sMizoram!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587963660559!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:41:09', '2020-04-27 15:41:09'),
(33, 'India', 'Tripura', NULL, 'tripura', '', '', NULL, '1587962647_5ea663177fffc.jpeg', NULL, '1587962647_5ea6631782ad5.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>The tiniest baby of the northeastern states, Tripura is surrounded in the north, south and west by Bangladesh and in the east by Assam and Mizoram. Although poverty stricken and facing civic as well as political issues more often than not, Tripura boasts one of the highest literacy rate in India. Other than this, Tripura also has many (many and many) kinds of gardens. This state not only offers a picturesque site, but with its fusion of modern and traditional culture, it also has a peculiar attraction for those who seek the fusion of both the mainstream and the secluded. There is much to discover in this small yet intriguing state and each can find their own unique experience on a trip to Tripura.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>Like in on other northeastern states, people in Tripura largely consume rice and varied kinds of meat. When it comes to Tripura, one cannot mention food without Mui Borok, the traditional dish of the state. Bangui rice, fish stews, food cooked in less oil with abundance of vegetables, Tripura cuisine really does scream comfort food. Even though not majorly unique, the food of this state is everything you need after a days worth of good travel and exploring. Apart from the traditional dishes, Tripura cuisine is also influenced by its neighbor Bangladesh, Assam and the other northeastern states. Many prominent dishes or their modified versions can be found in this state.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>Due to the increasing population of migrants, the culture in Tripura is influenced both by the native people as well as Bengali culture. The languages spoken in the state and the diversity among the people are thus greatly rich and diverse, and yet complimentary. When it comes to craft, Tripura notably exceeds in bamboo and cane handicrafts. This not only depicts the creative streak of the native people but also helps in generating revenue. Songs and music are also deeply intricate parts of this wholesome culture. Be it a festival, a wedding or any other day, Tripurites will have a song for it all!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Agartala</li><li>Dharamnagar</li><li>Unakoti- Timeless ruins</li><li>Sepahijala Wildlife Sanctuary</li><li>Ujjjayanta Palace</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d935010.6415472458!2d91.18237314199364!3d23.733635162157746!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3753b566f6c1a285%3A0x14dd7ae7453fff74!2sTripura!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587963876135!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:44:07', '2020-04-27 15:44:07'),
(34, 'India', 'Punjab', NULL, 'punjab', '', '', NULL, '1587962975_5ea6645f47299.jpeg', NULL, '1587962975_5ea6645f48f96.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>When it comes to tourism, Punjab tends to be quite an underrated choice. This gem of a state is famous for numerous purposes including the religious sentiments of many that this place connects with. But many of its picturesque as well as intriguing parts yet remain largely unexplored by the masses. Also referred to as the land of five rivers this state is surrounded by Jammu and Kashmir, Himachal Pradesh, Haryana and Rajasthan, hence it carries a mixture of fusion cultures along with its own unique historic traditions. This makes Punjab a perfect hub for those who are looking to indulge in a soul-searching yet fun vacation trip.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>Punjabi cuisine is one of those rare cuisines that have made their way onto your table more often than not, many a times without you even realizing it. The food from Punjab has scattered all round the nation, fused with spices and recipes particular to a place making it a unique experience for each individual. Since Punjab is a state dominant in agriculture practice, the food largely consists of rice and numerous kinds of pulses along with high demands of meat and dairy products. The one thing, which is highly consistent in many dishes of Punjab, is the gravy and curry texture that is given to many of the items. This makes many different ingredients complement each other nicely, giving our taste buds a unique and flavorful experience. The spices are used extensively in this cuisine in order to counter the fried nature of most of the food items. If you wish to base your travel plans around heavenly food, Punjab is the perfect place to begin with!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>Punjab has a culture, which promotes romance and a love for life in all its art. Be it Bhangra, a dance form particularly attributed to this state which requires high levels of energy and agile movements, or be it poetry and folklore, of which there are countless based on any situation you can think of, everything exudes an affinity for love and life. When it comes to art and craft, one can easily observe the blast of color in every piece of handiwork. The culture and traditions of Punjab are as upbeat as the people here, and hence it is the perfect getaway if you need your spirits lifted.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Amritsar</li><li>Chandigarh</li><li>Patiala</li><li>Pathankot</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3502061.890470402!2d73.15741805173222!3d30.998870326747056!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x391964aa569e7355%3A0x8fbd263103a38861!2sPunjab!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587964191412!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:49:35', '2020-04-27 15:49:35'),
(36, 'India', 'Uttar pradesh', NULL, 'uttar-pradesh', '', '', NULL, '1587963242_5ea6656a153a3.jpeg', NULL, '1587963242_5ea6656a17d0d.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>Uttar Pradesh is the most populous state in India, with over 200 million inhabitants and 75 districts. Due to its vastness geographically and connectivity with Rajasthan, Delhi, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Uttarakhand, Bihar, Madhya Pradesh, Jharkhand and Chattisgarh, the culture significantly varies throughout the state. It is difficult to label Uttar Pradesh thus, since it provides many contrasting yet complementary experiences to its tourists. UP is also the state, which receives the largest number of international and national tourists every year, making it a hotspot for tourist destination. This state is a dream-come-true for those who are explorers through and through. So if you are in a mood to discover something new, or just clear your mind and fill it with vibrancy, a trip to Uttar Pradesh will do you good.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>The diverse inhabitants and their diverse history have a direct correlation with the diverse cuisines that this state has to offer. One cannot pin point a particular kind of taste to the cuisines of Uttar Pradesh. Ranging from sweet, to spicy, to subtle, this place has something to offer for every kind of craving. The dishes from Uttar Pradesh are almost equally inclined towards both vegetarian and non-vegetarian. And both are equally lip-smacking! Tunday kebab, Kulcha-NIhari, Tehri, Batti Chokha, Bedhai, Petha, Malpua, these dishes are literal comfort on a platter and these are just to name a few. Uttar Pradesh is equally mesmerizing as Punjab when it comes to food. To taste the authentic recipes of these dishes, and to experience a whole new world of culinary art, plan your next visit to this one of a kind place!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>Literature, cinema, dance, theatre, art, music, Uttar Pradesh is an abundance of culture and traditions followed since time immemorial which are constantly being refined and practiced throughout the region. Due to the influence of many different historical additions to this state, the traditions of this place are a beautiful amalgamation that gives Uttar Pradesh its unique identity which is truly unmatched. From religious destinations like Varanasi and Mathura, to historical towns like Sarnath and Khushinagar, this state has hidden gems for everone! The architecture of this state differs greatly from region to region and boasts a refined art that has existed since centuries back. Various languages also have a deep-rooted history here, such as Urdu, Braj, Awadhi, Hindi and literature and art related to the development of these languages can be found in this state.&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Agra</li><li>Varanasi</li><li>Vrindavan</li><li>Lucknow</li><li>Allahabad</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d7276029.722307557!2d76.38912593265447!3d27.069673220557824!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39994e9f7b4a09d3%3A0xf6a5476d3617249d!2sUttar%20Pradesh!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587964415944!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:54:02', '2020-04-27 15:54:02'),
(37, 'India', 'Bihar', NULL, 'bihar', '', '', NULL, '1587963451_5ea6663b67eef.jpeg', NULL, '1587963451_5ea6663b6a802.jpeg', NULL, '<h2>About</h2><p>Bihar is a state, which is deeply rooted in tradition and culture. Home to the Ganges, Bihar is not only scenic but also has a serene atmosphere and a very down-to-earth environment. In ancient India, this state also boasted the title of the center of power and learning. The birthplace of Maurya dynasty as well as Buddhism, Bihar has a vast historical importance not only in India but globally as well. Although not highly developed in terms of infrastructure and economy, this state still has so much to offer when it comes to knowledge and spirituality. Not only this, but Bihar also has an amalgamation of many different cultural backgrounds which makes it a rich hub of diversity and contrasting traditions. If you wish to have a raw and intellectually fulfilling backpacking trip, Bihar is one place that you should rediscover.&nbsp;</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h2>Food</h2><p>Bihari cuisine is especially unique and one of a kind. From fried to baked, from sweet to sour, this cuisine has extreme variations to please everyone. The food is not only scrumptious, but it is also notable because of its comparative healthy nature even though it tastes sinfully delicious. Although heavy in carbs, the food in this state is generally prepared using substitute ingredients, which are richer in proteins and fibres. From Balushahi and Pantua to mutton kebabs and litti chokha, you cannot limit the variety of this cuisine into a particular category. Many dishes of Uttar Pradesh are famous all over India, but many are still limitedly discovered. To take ones taste buds for a ride, a trip to Bihar is an absolute necessity.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h2>Culture</h2><p>When one talks of Bihar and the culture it displays, the mention of Mithila painting style is never far behind. Although Bihar boasts numerous styles of painting, Mithila style, also known as Madhubani art, is the most famous type of painting style of this state. It was traditionally a painting done during occasions on the walls of huts and households, but later on the art began to appear on fabrics, handmade papers and then canvas as well. Apart from this, Bihar is also a treasure chest of world class music, poetry, and prose. Due to the diverse languages present in this state, literature and music originated from here have gathered a vast audience throughout the country. The multilingual aspect, the bulk of history connected with it, as well as the spiritual and religious getaways this state has to offer are reason enough to divulge in a trip to Bihar at least once!</p><h2>&nbsp;</h2><h2>Sightseeing</h2><ul><li>Bodh Gaya</li><li>Nalanda</li><li>Sitamarhi</li><li>Valmiki National Park</li><li>Navlakha Palace</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3675629.277047704!2d83.55830839228621!3d25.886530237465575!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x39ed5844f0bb6903%3A0x57ad3fed1bbae325!2sBihar!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587964655844!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 15:57:31', '2020-10-03 12:57:03'),
(38, 'India', 'Ladakh', NULL, 'ladakh', '', '', NULL, '1587963788_5ea6678c214ae.jpeg', NULL, '1587963788_5ea6678c2322d.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>Ladakh is a Union Territory in northern India, and was previously a region of Jammu and Kashmir. The land of high passes, as it is sometimes referred to as, has garnered significant attention due to its remote mountainous range, which provides a scenic beauty that is unrivaled. This region is influenced greatly by Tibetan culture and is thus endearingly labeled as Little Tibet. Ladakh is one of the least populated regions in the northern area, so it not only serves as an excellent tourist attraction due to its aesthetics, but also as the perfect place to take a retreat. Be it a spiritual getaway or just a withdrawal from ones day to day life, Ladakh is the go-to place when it comes to a little soul searching.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>Ladakh food is greatly derived from Tibetan cuisine since the predominant culture of the area is the same. The cuisine of Ladakh is also much influenced by the extremely cold weather that it experiences throughout the year. The level of spices used in the dishes is higher in order to tackle the cold. Meat and beef are prominent ingredients in many dishes, making Ladakhs cuisine rich in nutritional value. The cuisine also boasts recipes which are mostly broth based. Various kinds of soups and stews are sometimes prepared with flour dumplings and at other times with mutton or beef. All the recipes are seasoned graciously with numerous vegetables thus giving the dishes a unique texture and flavor. Dairy products are also used significantly to prepare side dishes that complement the food in Ladakh. These preparations, like gur gur cha, provide high energy and warmth. Ladakh cuisine is what one can imagine as comfort food through and through!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>The culture of Tibet is more inclined towards that of Tibet and Central Asia than towards India. The whole population of the land is either Buddhist or Muslim, although a very small ratio of Hindus also reside the area. Agricultural and pastoral lifestyle is the mainstream source of earning, but the trade is remote and is majorly confined to nearby areas only. Apart from cultivating wheat, barley, etc, the inhibitants of Ladakh also grow apples and apricots on the lower altitudes. Sheep rearing is one of the mainstream occupations and provides the renowned pashmina wool. Ladakh is also famous for its unique fauna, which comprises of red bear, ibex, snow leopard, antelope, gazelle, wild sheep etc. It is also rich in numerous semi-precious stones as well as copper and gold. If you wish to discover a tradition, which differs greatly from that of the rest of India, Ladakh is the best-secluded reprise for you!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Kargil</li><li>Zanskar Valley</li><li>Khardung-la Pass</li><li>Magnetic Hill</li><li>Shanti Stupa</li></ul>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3301.3209738813957!2d77.57957231470246!3d34.16371041929625!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x38fdeb3f7909dfb5%3A0x88202f821461c0e6!2sLadakh!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587965010746!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 16:03:08', '2020-04-27 16:03:08'),
(39, 'India', 'Chhattisgarh', NULL, 'chhattisgarh', '', '', NULL, '1587964036_5ea66884ac12e.jpeg', NULL, '1587964036_5ea66884ade16.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>One of the fastest developing states in India as well as the source of the countrys major portion of electricity, steel and coal, Chhattisgarh is not only a powerhouse but also a hidden gem of culture and potential. Situated at the heart of India, this state holds rare wildlife and natural diversity that attract numerous tourists annually. Apart from a rich geography, Chhattisgarh also boasts a rich historical background. Carved temples, monasteries, palaces, caves, rock paintings, waterfalls, hot springs, the list goes on and on if we talk about the treasures that this state holds. Wildlife sanctuaries and national parks are also abundant in Chhattisgarh. In fact, Raipur, a district of this state, is the home to the first man-made jungle safari. This state is a mix pot for diverse interests and definitely needs to be on your travel list!</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Food</h4><p>Agriculture is also a major sector in Chhattisgarh and hence the inclusion of various cereals in its cuisine is a given. Rice, Bajra and Jawar based dishes are prominent in the state, although one can easily find many dishes which have been inspired by their neighboring states thus providing the cuisine of Chhattisgarh with a fresh variety. The food in this state leans pretty heavily towards fried. All the major dishes are either fried or prepared using high amounts of oil and ghee, although the use of ingredients like besan instead of maida results in balancing out the high fats level. The main courses are usually accompanied by numerous side dishes, including dessert. The amount of spices is also generous in most of the food items. If you are a foodie through and through, then Chhattisgarh is the ultimate destination for you to discover a brand new cuisine.</p><h4>&nbsp;</h4><h4>Culture</h4><p>Chhattisgarh, just like many other states of India, is a mixture of people hailing from many different regions, and thus belonging to different religions. Being almost at the center, it serves as a prime location for the diverse cultures to coexist. Literature and theatre are very much celebrated in this state. Being historically of importance, Chhattisgarh had started documenting the development of its culture through these mediums from a long time ago. When it comes to art and craft, Kosa silk and lost wax art are two things for which this state is known. Chhattisgarh also boasts a wide variety of dance styles each of which has evolved from a different tradition or culture of the state. Discovering all the aspects and the mingling of the various religious sects and their cultures that are present in the state should be an exciting recreational activity if you are a curiosity buff.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Sightseeing</h4><ul><li>Barnawapara Wildlife Sanctuary</li><li>Shri Rajiv Lochan Mandir</li><li>Chitrakot Waterfalls</li><li>Mahakoshal Art Gallery</li></ul>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3815846.384741192!2d80.07574290474389!3d20.935944041016107!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x3a261f16c67a8bad%3A0x5c23f412fb179d95!2sChhattisgarh!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1587965257787!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-04-27 16:07:16', '2020-04-27 16:07:16'),
(40, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', NULL, 'himachal-pradesh', '', '', NULL, '1588328076_5eabf68cc255c.jpeg', NULL, '1588328076_5eabf68cc4efa.jpeg', NULL, '<h4>About</h4><p>Himachal Pradesh is a scenic state located alongside the Great Himalayas.&nbsp;&nbsp;It\'s home to breath-taking mountain towns and resorts such as Dalhousie. The state has a strong Tibetan presence. It can be witnessed through the Buddhist temples and monasteries, as well as its vibrant Tibetan New Year celebrations. Home of Dalai Lama, Himachal Pradesh is the land of brewing rich culture and enchanting natural beauty. The region is also well known for its adventurous angle, offering activities like trekking, climbing and skiing areas.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Food</h4><p>Himachal Pradesh is known for its scrumptious cuisine.&nbsp;From the road vendors to the authentic cafes and restaurant, the Himachali people will pour their heart out in their dishes.&nbsp;The surrounding states of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://food.ndtv.com/food-drinks/5-best-lassi-recipes-the-creamy-summer-cooler-from-punjab-1402630\">Punjab</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://food.ndtv.com/opinions/the-tale-of-thukpa-what-lends-flavour-to-this-comforting-noodle-soup-1277458\">Tibet&nbsp;</a>have a deep influence. Most of their dishes are slow-cooked imparting a unique flavour and aroma and a lot of their preparations are also fermented. The cuisine is predominantly homely yet rich and intense. Some Himachali wonders are madra, tudkiya bhath, and chaha gosht. And to enjoy the snowy hill views better, have babroo and mittha for dessert.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4>Culture</h4><p>Himachal Pradesh&nbsp;is a multi religious, multicultural as well as a multilingual state like other Indian states. The official language of this state is&nbsp;Pahari&nbsp;and&nbsp;Hindi.&nbsp;Apart from all festivals celebrated in India there are some unique festivals of Himachal Pradesh.&nbsp;Some of these fairs and festivals in the upper regions are the Kullu Dussehra, Shivratri Fair&nbsp;(Mandi),&nbsp;Shoolini Mela&nbsp;(Solan) and&nbsp;Minjar Fair&nbsp;(Chamba).&nbsp;Music and dance beautifully reflect the culture and the tradition of Himachal Pradesh. Some of them are are Losar and Shona, Chuksa. The people of Himachal Pradesh mostly wear woolens, as its best suited to the climate.&nbsp;Scarves and shawls are ubiquitous with the women while the men can be found in various types of Kurtas and the typical Himachal cap.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Sightseeing</strong></h4><ul><li>Rohtang La</li><li>Solang Nala</li><li>Hidimba Devi temple</li><li>Spiti Valley</li><li>The Great Himalayan National Park</li><li>Chandra Taal</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p>', '<iframe src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3472279.549286716!2d75.05168106520073!3d31.800529756338427!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x390453c367f901f7%3A0x7cfe04c5564b7725!2sHimachal%20Pradesh!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sin!4v1588329142330!5m2!1sen!2sin\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" frameborder=\"0\" style=\"border:0;\" allowfullscreen=\"\" aria-hidden=\"false\" tabindex=\"0\"></iframe>', '2020-05-01 21:14:36', '2020-05-01 21:14:36'),
(55, 'USA', 'New York', NULL, 'new-york', '', '', NULL, 'skyline-1983321-1920-1618919141159991.jpeg', 'skyline-1983321_1920', 'skyline-1983321-1920-1618919142740803.jpeg', 'skyline-1983321_1920', '<p>ascsacsasaac</p>', 'sacssccs', '2021-04-20 17:15:42', '2021-04-20 17:15:42'),
(62, 'India', 'Rajasthan', 'Jaipur', 'jaipur', 'Tourist Attractions in Jaipur', 'Jaipur tourism Jaipur attractions Jaipur sightseeing Pink city of India Forts and palaces in Jaipur Jaipur heritage aipur architecture Hawa Mahal Amber Fort City Palace Jaipur Jantar Mantar Jaipur Nahargarh Fort Jaigarh Fort Albert Hall Museum Jal Mahal B', 'Jaipur, the capital city of Rajasthan, is famous for its rich history, vibrant culture, and magnificent architectural marvels. Several tourist places in Jaipur attract visitors from all around the world.', 'rajasthan-thumbanil-image-1682682194950695.jpeg', 'rajasthan_thumbanil_image', 'rajasthan-banner-iamge-1682682196590888.png', 'rajasthan_banner_iamge', '<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jaipur, the capital city of Rajasthan, is famous for its rich history, vibrant culture, and magnificent architectural marvels. Several tourist places in Jaipur attract visitors from all around the world. Here are some of the most popular ones:</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Hawa</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Mahal</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">: Hawa Mahal is a five-storied palace that was built in 1799 by Maharaja Sawai Pratap Singh. The palace\'s unique design features 953 small windows called jharokhas that allow the royal ladies to observe the everyday life of the city without being seen. The palace\'s pink sandstone facade is decorated with intricate carvings and features a beautiful blend of Rajput and Mughal architectural styles.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">City Palace</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">: City Palace was built by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II in the 18th century and is a magnificent complex of courtyards, gardens, and buildings. The palace complex has been converted into a museum that showcases the rich cultural heritage of Rajasthan. The museum displays royal costumes, weapons, paintings, and artifacts from the past. The palace\'s architecture is a beautiful blend of Mughal and Rajasthani styles.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jantar Mantar:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Jantar Mantar is an astronomical observatory that was built by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II in the 18th century. The observatory features several unique and accurate instruments for measuring time, predicting eclipses, and tracking stars\' movements. The observatory is a testament to Maharaja\'s interest in astronomy and his dedication to the study of the cosmos.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Amber Fort:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Amber Fort is a beautiful blend of Hindu and Mughal architecture that was built by Raja Man Singh I in the 16th century. The fort features several palaces, temples, and courtyards, including the Sheesh Mahal, which is entirely covered in mirrors. The fort\'s architecture and design are a testament to the grandeur of the Rajput kings of Rajasthan.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jaigarh Fort:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Jaigarh Fort is a formidable structure that was built by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II. The fort served as a military fortress and a palace and is located on a hilltop overlooking the city of Jaipur. The fort houses several interesting features, including the world\'s largest cannon on wheels, which was used to defend the fort against invaders.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Nahargarh Fort:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Nahargarh Fort is a beautiful fort that was built by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II in the 18th century. The fort is located on the Aravalli Hills and offers stunning views of the city of Jaipur. The fort served as a retreat for the royal family and was used for hunting parties. The fort\'s architecture and design are a beautiful blend of Rajput and Mughal styles.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jal Mahal:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Jal Mahal is a beautiful palace located in the middle of Man Sagar Lake in Jaipur. The palace was built in the 18th century by Maharaja Jai Singh II and is a stunning example of Rajput and Mughal architecture. Visitors can take a boat ride around the lake to get a closer view of the palace.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Albert Hall Museum: The </strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Albert Hall Museum is a beautiful building that was designed by Sir Swinton Jacob and opened to the public in 1887. The museum houses a large collection of artifacts, including sculptures, paintings, and carpets. The museum\'s architecture is a beautiful blend of Indo-Saracenic and European styles.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Birla Mandir:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Birla Mandir is a beautiful temple located on the foothills of Moti Dungri. The temple was built in 1988 by the Birla family and is dedicated to Lord Vishnu and Goddess Lakshmi. The temple\'s architecture is a beautiful blend of modern and traditional styles.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Sisodia Rani Garden:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Sisodia Rani Garden is a beautiful garden located on the outskirts of Jaipur. The garden was built in the 18th century by Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II for his queen, Sisodia Rani. The garden features several beautiful fountains, pavilions, and murals that depict the love story of Radha and Krishna.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Galta Ji Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Galta Ji Temple, also known as the Monkey Temple, is a beautiful temple located on the outskirts of Jaipur. The temple is dedicated to Lord Hanuman and is surrounded by a natural spring that is believed to have healing properties. Visitors can also see several monkeys roaming around the temple premises.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Chokhi Dhani:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Chokhi Dhani is a cultural village that offers visitors a glimpse into the traditional lifestyle of Rajasthan. The village features several traditional huts, live music and dance performances, and a variety of delicious Rajasthani cuisine. Visitors can also enjoy camel rides and other traditional activities in the village.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Govind Dev Ji Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Govind Dev Ji Temple is a beautiful temple located in the City Palace complex. The temple is dedicated to Lord Krishna and was built in the 18th century by Maharaja Sawai Pratap Singh. The temple is known for its beautiful architecture and daily arti and bhog ceremonies.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Patrika Gate</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">: Patrika Gate is a beautiful structure located near Jawahar Circle in Jaipur. The gate is dedicated to the vibrant culture and heritage of Rajasthan and is adorned with beautiful hand-painted murals that depict the city\'s history, traditions, and folklore.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jaipur Wax Museum:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Jaipur Wax Museum is a unique museum located near Nahargarh Fort. The museum features wax statues of several famous personalities, including Bollywood stars, historical figures, and world leaders. Visitors can take photographs with the wax statues and learn about the personalities they represent.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Anokhi Museum of Hand Printing</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">: Anokhi Museum of Hand Printing is a beautiful museum located in the historic Amber Fort. The museum showcases the art of hand printing and features several exhibits that trace the history and evolution of hand printing techniques in India. Visitors can also participate in workshops and learn about the various printing techniques.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jawahar Kala Kendra</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">: Jawahar Kala Kendra is a cultural center located in the heart of Jaipur. The center features several art galleries, exhibition spaces, and a beautiful amphitheater. The center hosts several cultural events, including music and dance performances, art exhibitions, and theater performances.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Raj Mandir Cinema:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Raj Mandir Cinema is a famous movie theater located in the heart of Jaipur. The theater is known for its beautiful architecture, which features a stunning chandelier and a colorful ceiling. Visitors can enjoy watching Bollywood and Hollywood movies in this iconic cinema.</span></li></ul><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=26.87586613094959%2C75.83057650000003&z=11', '2023-04-28 11:43:17', '2023-04-28 11:43:17');
