(63, 'India', 'Rajasthan', 'Jodhpur', 'jodhpur', 'Jodhpur Tourist Attractions', 'Jodhpur tourist attractions Mehrangarh Fort Umaid Bhawan Palace Jaswant Thada Ghanta Ghar Mandore Gardens Kaylana Lake Balsamand Lake Chamunda Mata Temple Osian Desert Safari Jodhpur bazaars Blue City of India Rajasthan tourism Historical places in Jodhpu', 'Welcome to Jodhpur, a city in the western state of Rajasthan, India. Jodhpur is a land of magnificent forts, palaces, and temples, each with its unique story. Let us take you through the must-visit tourist places in Jodhpur.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Welcome to Jodhpur, a city in the western state of Rajasthan, India. Jodhpur is a land of magnificent forts, palaces, and temples, each with its unique story. Let us take you through the must-visit tourist places in Jodhpur.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Mehrangarh Fort -</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Built by Rao Jodha in 1459, this fort is perched on a hilltop and provides a stunning view of the city. It houses several palaces, courtyards, and museums, giving visitors a glimpse into the royal past of Jodhpur.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jaswant Thada</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - A mausoleum built by Maharaja Sardar Singh in memory of his father, Jaswant Singh II. Made of white marble, it is also known as the \"Taj Mahal of Marwar.\"</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Umaid Bhawan Palace</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - Built by Maharaja Umaid Singh in 1929, this palace is a symbol of an architectural marvel and a blend of Indian and Western styles. It is now converted into a heritage hotel and museum.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Mandore Gardens</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - This is the ancient capital of Marwar, and the gardens house several temples, cenotaphs, and statues. The most prominent one is the Chattris, a group of royal cenotaphs that reflect the architectural brilliance of the bygone era.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Clock Tower</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - Built by Maharaja Sardar Singh, this tower stands tall in the heart of the city and is a popular landmark. It is surrounded by a bustling market that offers a variety of items, including handicrafts, spices, and textiles.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Balsamand Lake</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - This artificial lake was built in the 13th century by Balak Rao Parihar. It is surrounded by lush green gardens and orchards and is a popular spot for picnics and boating.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Sardar Government Museum -</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Located within the Umaid Public Gardens, this museum showcases the cultural and historical heritage of Jodhpur. It has a collection of artifacts, paintings, and sculptures from different periods.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Chamunda Mata Temple -</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> This temple is dedicated to Goddess Chamunda, who is considered to be an incarnation of Goddess Durga. It is situated on a hilltop and offers a panoramic view of the city.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Rao Jodha Desert Rock Park</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - Spread over 72 hectares, this park was created in 2006 to restore and promote the natural ecology of the Thar Desert. It has a variety of desert plants and animals, and visitors can also go on nature trails and birdwatching tours.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Osian</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - Located about 65 km from Jodhpur, Osian is an ancient town known for its temples and sand dunes. It has several Jain and Hindu temples that date back to the 8th and 11th centuries and are famous for their intricate carvings and architecture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jodhpur is a city steeped in history and culture, and each of these tourist places holds great significance. Mehrangarh Fort and Jaswant Thada offer insights into the royal past of Jodhpur, while Umaid Bhawan Palace is a reflection of the grandeur of the Rajput era. Mandore Gardens showcase the architectural brilliance of ancient times, and the Clock Tower is a hub of activity that showcases the vibrant spirit of Jodhpur. So pack your bags and head to Jodhpur, a city that will leave you mesmerized with its beauty, history, and culture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=26.270391913775946%2C73.03054325&z=12', '2023-04-28 19:35:13', '2023-04-28 19:35:13'),
(64, 'India', 'Rajasthan', NULL, NULL, 'JAISALMER TOURIST ATTRACTIONS', 'Jaisalmer Fort Patwon Ki Haveli Sam Sand Dunes Gadisar Lake Bada Bagh Jain Temples Kuldhara Abandoned Village Desert Safari Camel rides Thar Heritage Museum Salim Singh Ki Haveli Tazia Tower', 'Welcome to Jaisalmer, a city in the western Indian state of Rajasthan, also known as the \"Golden City.\" Jaisalmer is famous for its sandstone forts, palaces, and temples which are a testament to the rich cultural heritage of Rajasthan. Let us take you through the must-visit tourist places in Jaisalmer.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> </strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Welcome to Jaisalmer, a city in the western Indian state of Rajasthan, also known as the \"Golden City.\" Jaisalmer is famous for its sandstone forts, palaces, and temples which are a testament to the rich cultural heritage of Rajasthan. Let us take you through the must-visit tourist places in Jaisalmer.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jaisalmer Fort</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - Built by the Bhati Rajput ruler Jaisal in the 12th century, this fort stands tall on a hilltop and is one of the largest forts in the world. The fort has several palaces, temples, and havelis (traditional mansions) that are a perfect example of Rajasthani architecture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Patwon Ki Haveli</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - This haveli was built by the wealthy merchant Guman Chand Patwa in the 19th century. It is a cluster of five havelis and is famous for its exquisite architecture and intricate carvings.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Gadisar Lake</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> - This artificial