(70, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Manali', 'manali', 'MANALI TOURIST PLACES', 'Manali, Himachal Pradesh, India, tourism, travel, mountains, adventure, trekking, skiing, honeymoon, backpacking, scenic beauty, nature, adventure sports, Rohtang Pass, Solang Valley.', 'Manali is a beautiful hill station located in the state of Himachal Pradesh, India. The town is surrounded by snow-capped mountains, lush green valleys, and glistening rivers, making it a popular tourist destination. Manali is known for its natural beauty, adventure activities, and rich cultural heritage. In this blog, we will take you through 20 of the best tourist places in Manali, including their history, significance, and things to do.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Manali is a beautiful hill station located in the state of Himachal Pradesh, India. The town is surrounded by snow-capped mountains, lush green valleys, and glistening rivers, making it a popular tourist destination. Manali is known for its natural beauty, adventure activities, and rich cultural heritage. In this blog, we will take you through 20 of the best tourist places in Manali, including their history, significance, and things to do.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Hadimba Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Hadimba Temple is an ancient temple located in the midst of a dense cedar forest in Manali. The temple is dedicated to the demon goddess Hadimba, who was the wife of Bhima, one of the five Pandavas from the Hindu epic, Mahabharata. The temple was built in the 16th century and is known for its unique architecture, which features intricately carved wooden doors and walls. The temple is surrounded by cedar trees, and it is a popular place of worship for locals and tourists alike.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Vashisht Hot Water Springs and Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> The Vashisht Temple is located in the village of Vashisht, just a few kilometers from Manali. The temple is dedicated to Sage Vashisht, who is said to have meditated here. The temple is known for its hot water springs, which are believed to have healing properties. Visitors can take a dip in the hot water springs or attend the daily prayer services held at the temple.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Solang Valley:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Solang Valley is a picturesque valley located in the Kullu district of Himachal Pradesh. The valley is known for its snow-capped mountains, lush greenery, and adventure sports like skiing, paragliding, and zorbing. The valley is also home to several small villages where visitors can experience local culture and traditions.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Rohtang Pass:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Rohtang Pass is a high mountain pass located on the Pir Panjal Range of the Himalayas. The pass is known for its scenic beauty, snow-capped mountains, and adventure sports like skiing, snowboarding, and sledging. The pass is also an important trade route that connects the Kullu Valley to the Lahaul and Spiti Valleys.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Jogini Waterfall:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Jogini Waterfall is a picturesque waterfall located in Vashisht, just a few kilometers from Manali. The waterfall is surrounded by lush greenery, and visitors can take a dip in the cool water or go for a hike in the surrounding forests.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Manu Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Manu Temple is an ancient temple located in the old town of Manali. The temple is dedicated to the sage Manu, who is believed to be the creator of the world according to Hindu mythology. The temple is known for its wooden carvings and intricate architecture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Beas River:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> The Beas River is a beautiful river that flows through the Kullu Valley in Himachal Pradesh. The river is known for its scenic beauty, clear water, and adventure sports like rafting and kayaking. Visitors can also enjoy a leisurely walk along the riverbank or take a dip in the cool water.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Naggar Castle:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Naggar Castle is a historic castle located in Naggar, a small town near Manali. The castle was built in the 16th century by Raja Sidh Singh of Kullu and is known for its beautiful architecture and intricate wood carvings. The castle now houses a heritage hotel and a museum that showcases the rich culture and history of the Kullu Valley.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Manali Wildlife Sanctuary:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> The Manali Wildlife Sanctuary is a protected area located near Manali. The sanctuary is home to several species of animals like snow leopard, musk deer, and Himalayan black bear. Visitors can go on a trek through the sanctuary or go on a safari to spot these majestic animals in their natural habitat.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Himalayan</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> </span><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Nyingmapa Buddhist Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> The Himalayan Nyingmapa Buddhist Temple in Manali is a serene and beautiful temple built by the Tibetan community in the 1960s. It is a symbol of the rich Tibetan culture and heritage and is one of the most important Buddhist temples in the region. The temple features stunning murals, intricate carvings, and a large prayer wheel. The peaceful atmosphere and mesmerizing views of the surrounding mountains make it a must-visit for anyone interested in Buddhism or seeking inner peace.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Beas Kund:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> A popular trekking destination, Beas Kund is a high-altitude glacial lake located about 17 km from Manali. The trek to Beas Kund offers stunning views of the Dhauladhar and Pir Panjal ranges.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Manu Temple:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Located in the old town of Manali, Manu Temple is a beautiful shrine dedicated to the sage Manu. The temple\'s architecture is unique, with intricate wooden carvings and a pagoda-style roof.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Naggar Castle:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> Located about 20 km from Manali, Naggar Castle is a beautiful heritage site. The castle was built in the 15th century by the rulers of the Kullu Kingdom and is known for its stunning architecture and beautiful surroundings.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Van Vihar National Park:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\"> A popular picnic spot, Van Vihar National Park is located on the banks of the Beas River. The park is home to a variety of flora and fauna, such as deodar trees, birds, and butterflies.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">	</span></p><ul><li><strong style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Kothi</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">: A small village located about 16 km from Manali, Kothi is known for its stunning views of the Himalayas. The village is surrounded by snow-capped peaks and offers a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of Manali.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Manali is truly a paradise for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. With its scenic beauty, serene environment, and rich cultural heritage, the town has something to offer to everyone. Whether you are looking for a peaceful retreat or an action-packed adventure, Manali has it all. We hope this blog has helped you discover some of the best tourist places in Manali and inspired you to plan your next vacation to this beautiful hill station.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=32.239474281465895%2C77.18711979999999&z=14', '2023-04-28 19:54:26', '2023-04-28 19:54:26'),
(71, 'India', 'Karnataka', 'Bangaluru', 'bangaluru', 'BANGALORE TOURIST PLACES', 'garden city, silicon valley of India, Bengaluru, IT hub, tech city, cosmopolitan, multicultural, tourist attractions, historical monuments, temples, gardens, museums, street food, nightlife.', 'Bangalore, also known as Bengaluru, is a vibrant city in Southern India that is famous for its pleasant climate, green spaces, and bustling IT industry', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bangalore, also known as Bengaluru, is a vibrant city in Southern India that is famous for its pleasant climate, green spaces, and bustling IT industry. Here are some of the must-visit tourist places in Bangalore:</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Lalbagh Botanical Garden - Lalbagh Botanical Garden is a 240-acre garden that is home to over 1,000 species of plants and trees. It was originally laid out in the 18th century by Hyder Ali, the ruler of Mysore, and later expanded by his son Tipu Sultan. The garden is now a popular spot for picnics, jogging, and bird watching.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Bangalore Palace - Bangalore Palace is a stunning Tudor-style palace located in the heart of the city. It was built in 1887 by Chamaraja Wodeyar, the ruler of Mysore, and is now open to the public as a museum. The palace is known for its beautiful architecture and is a great place to learn about the city\'s history and culture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Cubbon Park - Cubbon Park is a sprawling park located in the heart of Bangalore. It was created in the late 19th century by the British and is now a popular spot for jogging, walking, and relaxing. The park is home to several important landmarks, including the State Central Library, the High Court of Karnataka, and the Attara Kacheri.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Tipu Sultan\'s Summer Palace - Tipu Sultan\'s Summer Palace is a beautiful palace located in the heart of Bangalore. It was built in the late 18th century by Tipu Sultan, the ruler of Mysore, and is now open to the public as a museum. The palace is known for its beautiful architecture and is a great place to learn about the history of the city.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Bangalore Fort - Bangalore Fort is a historic fort located in the heart of the city. It was built in the 16th century by Kempegowda, the founder of Bangalore, and later expanded by Tipu Sultan. The fort is now a popular tourist attraction and is known for its beautiful architecture and rich history.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bangalore is a city that is rich in history, culture, and natural beauty. Each of these places has its own unique story and significance, and visiting them will give you a deeper appreciation for the city\'s heritage and charm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jjdOnB91E1dK8dHGVI3h8cHWE40&hl=en_US&ll=12.868256918091575%2C78.04532570947269&z=9', '2023-04-28 19:57:05', '2023-04-28 19:57:05'),
(72, 'India', 'Telangana', 'Hyderabad', 'hyderabad', 'HYDERABAD TOURIST PLACES', 'Hyderabad, India, Charminar, Golconda Fort, Hussain Sagar Lake, Salar Jung Museum, Ramoji Film City, Mecca Masjid, Chowmahalla Palace, Laad Bazaar, Birla Mandir, Qutub Shahi Tombs, Nizam\'s Museum, Falaknuma Palace, Osman Sagar Lake, Nehru Zoological Park,', 'Hyderabad, also known as the \"City of Pearls,\" is a bustling city in Southern India that is famous for its rich history, culture, and cuisine.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hyderabad, also known as the \"City of Pearls,\" is a bustling city in Southern India that is famous for its rich history, culture, and cuisine. Here are some of the must-visit tourist places in Hyderabad:</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Charminar - Charminar is a historic monument that is the symbol of Hyderabad. It was built in 1591 by Muhammad Quli Qutb Shah, the fifth ruler of the Qutb Shahi dynasty, and is now a popular tourist attraction. The monument is known for its beautiful architecture and is a great place to learn about the city\'s history.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Golconda Fort - Golconda Fort is a historic fort that was built in the 13th century by the Kakatiya dynasty. It was later expanded by the Qutb Shahi dynasty and was once a center of diamond trade. The fort is now a popular tourist attraction and is known for its beautiful architecture and rich history.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Salar Jung Museum - Salar Jung Museum is a popular museum located in the heart of Hyderabad. It was established in 1951 and is home to one of the largest collections of art, artifacts, and antiques in the world. The museum is known for its impressive collection of Indian art, European art, and Islamic art.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Chowmahalla Palace - Chowmahalla Palace is a historic palace located in the heart of Hyderabad. It was built in the 18th century by the Nizams of Hyderabad and was once the seat of the Asaf Jahi dynasty. The palace is known for its beautiful architecture and is a great place to learn about the history of the city.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Ramoji Film City - Ramoji Film City is a popular tourist attraction located on the outskirts of Hyderabad. It is one of the largest film studios in the world and is known for its impressive sets, rides, and attractions. The film city is a great place to learn about the film industry and experience the magic of movies.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hyderabad is a city that is rich in history, culture, and natural beauty. Each of these places has its own unique story and significance, and visiting them will give you a deeper appreciation for the city\'s heritage and charm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=17.385043999999997%2C78.48667099999999&z=14', '2023-04-28 19:59:38', '2023-04-28 19:59:38'),
(73, 'India', 'West Bengal', NULL, NULL, 'KOLKATA TOURIST PLACES', 'Victoria Memorial, Howrah Bridge, Kalighat Temple, St. Paul\'s Cathedral, Marble Palace, Indian Museum, Dakshineswar Kali Temple, Belur Math, Mother House, and Fort William.', 'Kolkata, also known as the \"City of Joy,\" is the capital city of West Bengal, located in Eastern India. Kolkata is a city that blends tradition with modernity, and is known for its rich culture, history, and intellectual legacy.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kolkata, also known as the \"City of Joy,\" is the capital city of West Bengal, located in Eastern India. Kolkata is a city that blends tradition with modernity, and is known for its rich culture, history, and intellectual legacy. Here are some of the must-visit tourist places in Kolkata:</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Victoria Memorial - The Victoria Memorial is a stunning white marble building located in the heart of Kolkata. It was built in memory of Queen Victoria and is now a museum dedicated to the city\'s history. The memorial is surrounded by lush gardens and is a great place to take a walk and enjoy the beautiful architecture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Howrah Bridge - The Howrah Bridge is an iconic landmark of Kolkata, built over the Hooghly River in 1943. It is one of the busiest bridges in the world and is a major symbol of Kolkata\'s connectivity and modernity.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Dakshineswar Kali Temple - The Dakshineswar Kali Temple is a famous Hindu temple located on the eastern bank of the Hooghly River. It was built in the mid-19th century by Rani Rashmoni, a philanthropist and devotee of Goddess Kali. The temple is known for its beautiful architecture and is an important place of pilgrimage for devotees of Goddess Kali.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">St. Paul\'s Cathedral - St. Paul\'s Cathedral is an Anglican cathedral located in Kolkata. It was built in 1847 and is known for its stunning Gothic architecture. The cathedral is a major landmark of Kolkata and is a great place to visit for history and architecture enthusiasts.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Park Street - Park Street is a famous shopping and dining destination in Kolkata. It is known for its vibrant nightlife and is a great place to explore the city\'s food and culture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kolkata is a city with a rich cultural heritage and a unique blend of tradition and modernity. Each of these places has its own history and significance, and visiting them will give you a deeper understanding of the city\'s culture and history.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=22.53545253511888%2C88.34735275000001&z=12', '2023-04-28 20:02:10', '2023-04-28 20:02:10'),
(74, 'India', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Agra', 'agra', 'Agra Touristy Places', 'Taj Mahal, Agra Fort, Fatehpur Sikri, Mughal architecture, UNESCO World Heritage Site, Mughal Empire, Akbar, Shah Jahan, Indian history, tourism in India.', 'Agra, a city located in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh, is home to one of the Seven Wonders of the World, the Taj Mahal. It is a city rich in history, culture, and architectural heritage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Agra, a city located in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh, is home to one of the Seven Wonders of the World, the Taj Mahal. It is a city rich in history, culture, and architectural heritage. Here are some must-visit tourist places in Agra:</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Taj Mahal</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Built by Emperor Shah Jahan in the 17th century in memory of his wife Mumtaz Mahal, the Taj Mahal is one of the most famous tourist attractions in India. It is a symbol of love and is known for its exquisite architecture and stunning beauty.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Agra Fort</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Also known as the Red Fort of Agra, it was built in the 16th century by Emperor Akbar. The fort showcases the rich history and architecture of the Mughal era and offers breathtaking views of the city.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fatehpur Sikri</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located on the outskirts of Agra, Fatehpur Sikri was the capital of the Mughal Empire for a brief period. The city is famous for its stunning architecture and is a perfect example of Mughal craftsmanship.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Itmad-Ud-Daulah</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Also known as the Baby Taj, it is a mausoleum built in the 17th century by Empress Nur Jahan in memory of her father. The monument showcases the intricate details of Mughal architecture and is known for its delicate inlay work.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mehtab Bagh</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located across the Yamuna River from the Taj Mahal, Mehtab Bagh offers a stunning view of the Taj Mahal at sunset. It is a perfect spot for photography and is a must-visit for nature lovers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jama Masjid</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Built by Emperor Shah Jahan in the 17th century, Jama Masjid is one of the largest mosques in India. It is a perfect example of Mughal architecture and is known for its intricate carvings and beautiful marble work.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Akbar\'s Tomb</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located in Sikandra, Akbar\'s Tomb is a magnificent mausoleum built in the 17th century in memory of Emperor Akbar. The tomb is a perfect blend of Mughal and Hindu architecture and is a must-visit for history buffs.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Chini ka Rauza</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Built in the 17th century, Chini ka Rauza is a tomb dedicated to the Persian poet and scholar Allama Afzal Khan Mullah. The tomb is known for its intricate Persian-style architecture and beautiful tilework.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Moti Masjid -</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> Also known as the Pearl Mosque, it was built by Emperor Shah Jahan in the 17th century. The mosque is made of white marble and is known for its beautiful architecture and intricate carvings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mariam\'s Tomb</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Built in the 17th century, Mariam\'s Tomb is a beautiful monument dedicated to Mariam Zamani, Emperor Akbar\'s wife. The tomb is a perfect example of Mughal architecture and is known for its beautiful carvings and intricate designs.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Agra is a city that is steeped in history and culture, and each of these tourist places holds great significance. The Taj Mahal is a testament to the eternal love between Emperor Shah Jahan and Mumtaz Mahal, while the Agra Fort showcases the rich history and architecture of the Mughal era. Fatehpur Sikri is a perfect example of Mughal craftsmanship, while Itmad-Ud-Daulah is known for its intricate inlay work. The Mehtab Bagh is a perfect spot to relax and enjoy the serene beauty of the city.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Agra is a city that will leave you mesmerized with its beauty, history, and culture. A visit to Agra is incomplete without experiencing the magnificent Taj Mahal and exploring the rich architectural heritage of the city. So pack your bags and head to Agra, a city that will leave you with memories that will last a lifetime.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=27.176201970079564%2C77.98001295000002&z=12', '2023-05-05 13:49:46', '2023-05-05 13:49:46'),
(75, 'India', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Varanasi', 'varanasi', 'VARANASI TOURIST PLACES', 'Varanasi, Kashi, Banaras, Ganges, Hinduism, spirituality, ancient city, ghats, temples, culture, history, pilgrimage.', 'Varanasi, also known as Banaras or Kashi, is a city in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is one of the world\'s oldest continuously inhabited cities and is considered one of the seven holiest cities in Hinduism. The city is situated on the banks of the river Ganges and is known for its spiritual and cultural significance. Varanasi is also known for its rich history, art, music, and literature. It attracts thousands of tourists from all over the world who come to experience the unique and vibrant culture of the city.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Varanasi, also known as Banaras or Kashi, is a city in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is one of the world\'s oldest continuously inhabited cities and is considered one of the seven holiest cities in Hinduism. The city is situated on the banks of the river Ganges and is known for its spiritual and cultural significance. Varanasi is also known for its rich history, art, music, and literature. It attracts thousands of tourists from all over the world who come to experience the unique and vibrant culture of the city.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Kashi Vishwanath Temple - Located in the heart of Varanasi, the Kashi Vishwanath Temple is one of the most famous and sacred temples in India. The temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is believed to be one of the 12 Jyotirlingas. It is a must-visit for anyone interested in Hindu mythology and culture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Dashashwamedh Ghat - Dashashwamedh Ghat is one of the most popular ghats in Varanasi and is famous for its evening aarti ceremony, where devotees offer prayers to the river Ganges. The ghat is also a great place to take a boat ride and enjoy the river and city views.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Sarnath - Sarnath is a famous Buddhist pilgrimage site located just a few kilometers from Varanasi. It is believed to be the place where Lord Buddha gave his first sermon after attaining enlightenment. The site houses a number of ancient Buddhist stupas and temples, including the famous Dhamek Stupa.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Banaras Hindu University - Banaras Hindu University is a renowned educational institution located in Varanasi. The university is known for its beautiful architecture, lush green campus, and excellent academic programs. It is a great place to visit for anyone interested in education and academia.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Ramnagar Fort - Ramnagar Fort is a historic fort located on the banks of the river Ganges. It was built in the 18th century by the kings of the Kashi Naresh dynasty and is known for its beautiful architecture and collection of ancient artifacts.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Manikarnika Ghat - Manikarnika Ghat is one of the most famous ghats in Varanasi and is known for its association with death and cremation rituals. It is believed that if a person is cremated here, they will attain salvation. The ghat is also a great place to observe the unique and vibrant culture of Varanasi.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Varanasi is a city with a rich cultural and spiritual heritage, and each of these places has its own unique history and significance. Visiting these places will give you a deeper understanding of the city\'s rich cultural heritage and spiritual significance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=25.3176452%2C82.9739144&z=12', '2023-05-05 13:51:53', '2023-05-05 13:51:53'),
(76, 'India', 'Maharashtra', NULL, NULL, 'MUMBAI TOURIST PLACES', 'Bollywood, Gateway of India, Marine Drive, Elephanta Caves, Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus, Haji Ali Dargah, Siddhivinayak Temple, Juhu Beach, Crawford Market, Sanjay Gandhi National Park', 'Mumbai, formerly known as Bombay, is a bustling city located on the west coast of India. It is India\'s financial, commercial, and entertainment capital, attracting thousands of visitors every year. Mumbai is known for its rich history, culture, and architecture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mumbai, formerly known as Bombay, is a bustling city located on the west coast of India. It is India\'s financial, commercial, and entertainment capital, attracting thousands of visitors every year. Mumbai is known for its rich history, culture, and architecture. Here are some of the must-visit tourist places in Mumbai:</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Gateway of India - The Gateway of India is an iconic monument located in South Mumbai. It was built in 1924 to commemorate the visit of King George V and Queen Mary to Mumbai. The monument is a great place to take a walk and enjoy the stunning views of the Arabian Sea.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Marine Drive - Marine Drive is a 3.6-kilometer-long boulevard located in South Mumbai. It is also known as the \"Queen\'s Necklace\" because of the way the streetlights resemble a necklace at night. The promenade is a great place to take a leisurely walk and enjoy the beautiful views of the Arabian Sea.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus - Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus, also known as Victoria Terminus, is a historic railway station located in South Mumbai. It was built in 1887 and is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The station is known for its beautiful Gothic architecture and is one of the busiest railway stations in India.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Elephanta Caves - The Elephanta Caves are a network of rock-cut caves located on the Elephanta Island, just a short ferry ride away from Mumbai. The caves are believed to have been built between the 5th and 8th centuries and are a UNESCO World Heritage Site. They are known for their beautiful sculptures and carvings, many of which are dedicated to Lord Shiva.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Juhu Beach - Juhu Beach is one of the most popular beaches in Mumbai. It is a great place to relax and enjoy the views of the Arabian Sea. The beach is also known for its street food and is a must-visit for anyone interested in trying out some authentic Mumbai cuisine.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mumbai is a city with a unique and vibrant culture, and each of these places has its own unique history and significance. Visiting these places will give you a deeper understanding of the city\'s rich cultural heritage and its importance as Indias financial and commercial center.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=19.0823590243553%2C72.88118614999998&z=10', '2023-05-05 14:00:24', '2023-05-05 14:00:24'),
(77, 'India', 'Punjab', 'Amritsar', 'amritsar', 'AMRITSAR TOURIST PLACES', 'Golden Temple, Wagah Border, Jallianwala Bagh, Punjab Cuisine, Amritsar, Chandigarh, Bhangra, Lassi, Patiala Peg, Punjabiyat, Sikhism, Partition Museum, Maharaja Ranjit Singh Museum, Anandpur Sahib, Bathinda Fort, Qila Mubarak.', 'Amritsar, a city in the northwestern Indian state of Punjab, is known for its rich cultural heritage and historical significance. It is home to the holiest shrine of Sikhism, the Golden Temple, and is also famous for its delicious food and vibrant street markets.', 'punjab-thumbnail-1683295443807367.jpeg', 'punjab_thumbnail', 'punjab-banner-1683295445375500.jpeg', 'punjab_banner', '<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Amritsar, a city in the northwestern Indian state of Punjab, is known for its rich cultural heritage and historical significance. It is home to the holiest shrine of Sikhism, the Golden Temple, and is also famous for its delicious food and vibrant street markets. Here are some must-visit tourist places in Amritsar:</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Golden Temple</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Also known as Sri Harmandir Sahib, it is the holiest shrine of Sikhism and one of the most famous tourist attractions in India. The temple is made of gold and marble and is surrounded by a sacred lake. It is a symbol of religious harmony and peace and attracts millions of visitors every year.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jallianwala Bagh</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located near the Golden Temple, Jallianwala Bagh is a public garden that has become a symbol of India\'s struggle for independence. It is the site of the infamous Jallianwala Bagh massacre that took place in 1919, where hundreds of innocent Indians were killed by British troops.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Wagah Border</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located on the India-Pakistan border, the Wagah Border is famous for its daily flag-lowering ceremony. The ceremony is a symbol of the rivalry between the two countries and attracts a large number of tourists.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Partition Museum</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - The Partition Museum is a museum dedicated to the history of the partition of India in 1947. It showcases the impact of the partition on people\'s lives and is a must-visit for history buffs.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Akal Takht</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located within the Golden Temple complex, the Akal Takht is the highest temporal seat of the Sikh religion. It is a symbol of the Sikh community\'s political and social aspirations and is a must-visit for anyone interested in the history and culture of Sikhism.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Durgiana Temple</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Located in the heart of Amritsar, the Durgiana Temple is a Hindu temple dedicated to Goddess Durga. The temple is known for its beautiful architecture and is a must-visit for anyone interested in Hindu mythology and culture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Maharaja Ranjit Singh Museum</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - The museum is located in the summer palace of Maharaja Ranjit Singh, the founder of the Sikh Empire. The museum houses a collection of artifacts, weapons, and paintings that showcase the history of the Sikh Empire and the life of Maharaja Ranjit Singh.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ram Bagh Garden</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Ram Bagh Garden is a beautiful garden that was built by the fourth Sikh Guru, Guru Ram Das. The garden is known for its beautiful floral arrangements, fountains, and well-manicured lawns.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gobindgarh Fort</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Gobindgarh Fort is a historic fort that was built by Maharaja Ranjit Singh in the early 19th century. The fort was later used as a British army garrison and has now been converted into a museum showcasing the history of Punjab and the Sikh Empire.</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Khalsa College</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> - Khalsa College is a historic college that was established in 1892. The college is known for its beautiful architecture and is a must-visit for anyone interested in the history of education in Punjab.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Amritsar is a city that is steeped in history and culture, and each of these tourist places holds great significance. The Golden Temple is a symbol of religious harmony and peace, while Jallianwala Bagh is a reminder of India\'s struggle for independence. The Wagah Border is a symbol of the rivalry between India and Pakistan, while the Partition Museum is a reminder of the horrors of partition. The Akal Takht is a symbol of the Sikh community\'s political and social aspirations.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Amritsar is also famous for its delicious food, including the famous Amritsari Kulcha and Chole Bhature. The city\'s vibrant street markets are a must-visit for anyone interested in shopping and experiencing the local culture.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Amritsar is a city that will leave you mesmerized with its beauty, history, culture, and delicious food. A visit to Amritsar is incomplete without experiencing the peacefulness of the Golden Temple, the poignant history of Jallianwala Bagh, and the unique culture of the city. So pack your bags and head to Amritsar, a city that will leave you with memories that will last a lifetime.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=31.038391640841414%2C75.41102069999998&z=7', '2023-05-05 14:04:05', '2023-05-05 14:04:05'),
(78, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', NULL, NULL, 'OOTY TOURIST PLACES', 'Ooty, Udhagamandalam, hill station, Nilgiris, botanical gardens, tea plantations, Doddabetta Peak, Ooty Lake, Pykara Falls, Mukurthi National Park.', 'Nestled in the Nilgiri Hills of Tamil Nadu, Ooty is a picturesque hill station that offers a perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. It is known for its pleasant climate, lush greenery, and scenic beauty. Ooty has a rich history and culture that is reflected in its numerous tourist attractions. In this article, we will explore some of the must-visit places in Ooty and their significance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nestled in the Nilgiri Hills of Tamil Nadu, Ooty is a picturesque hill station that offers a perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. It is known for its pleasant climate, lush greenery, and scenic beauty. Ooty has a rich history and culture that is reflected in its numerous tourist attractions. In this article, we will explore some of the must-visit places in Ooty and their significance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most popular tourist attractions in Ooty is the Botanical Garden. Established in 1847, the garden was originally created to serve as a hub for introducing new plant species. Today, it is a popular spot for nature enthusiasts and tourists. The garden is home to several exotic plants and flowers, including rare and endangered species. Visitors can also take a leisurely walk around the garden or enjoy a picnic with family and friends.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Another popular attraction is the Ooty Lake, which was built in 1824 by John Sullivan, the then-British Collector of Coimbatore. The lake is surrounded by lush green hills and provides a serene atmosphere for visitors to relax and enjoy the scenic beauty. Boating facilities are available for visitors, making it an ideal spot for families to spend some quality time together.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">The Doddabetta Peak is the highest peak in the Nilgiri Hills and offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding hills and valleys. It is a popular spot for trekking and hiking enthusiasts, and visitors can also enjoy the picturesque views from the telescope house located at the top of the peak.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">The Government Rose Garden, also known as the Jayalalithaa Rose Garden, is another must-visit place in Ooty. It is the largest rose garden in India and home to over 20,000 varieties. The garden is spread over 10 acres and also has several other exotic flowers and plants.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Finally, the Toy Train Ride is a must-do activity for visitors to Ooty. The train journey takes you through the scenic beauty of the Nilgiri Hills and offers stunning views of the surrounding landscapes. The train ride is a popular activity for families and couples alike and is a great way to explore the natural beauty of Ooty.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Ooty is a charming hill station with a rich history and culture and several must-visit tourist attractions. Whether you are a nature lover, a history enthusiast, or just looking for a peaceful getaway, Ooty has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=11.410203800000012%2C76.6950324&z=7', '2023-05-05 14:06:33', '2023-05-05 14:06:33'),
(79, 'India', 'Karnataka', 'Hampi', 'hampi', 'HAMPI TOURISTY PLACES', 'Hampi, Vijayanagara Empire, UNESCO World Heritage Site, Hampi Bazaar, Virupaksha Temple, Vittala Temple, Hemakuta Hill, Archaeological Museum, Monolithic Bull, Lotus Mahal, Tungabhadra River, Royal Enclosure.', 'Hampi is a UNESCO World Heritage site and one of the most popular tourist destinations in India. It was once the capital of the Vijayanagara Empire, and today, its ruins are a testament to the grandeur and opulence of that era.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hampi is a UNESCO World Heritage site and one of the most popular tourist destinations in India. It was once the capital of the Vijayanagara Empire, and today, its ruins are a testament to the grandeur and opulence of that era. Let\'s explore some of the must-visit places in Hampi.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Virupaksha Temple: This temple is one of the oldest and most important temples in Hampi. It was built in the 7th century and is dedicated to Lord Shiva. The temple has stunning architecture and intricate carvings, making it a must-visit for anyone interested in history and art.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hampi Bazaar: This is a vibrant street that was once a bustling marketplace during the Vijayanagara Empire. Today, it is a great place to shop for souvenirs and local handicrafts. The bazaar is lined with old buildings and temples, which add to its charm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Vittala Temple: This temple is famous for its iconic stone chariot, which is often featured in pictures of Hampi. It was built in the 16th century and is dedicated to Lord Vishnu. The temple is known for its intricate carvings and musical pillars, which produce different musical notes when struck.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Matanga Hill: This hill is the highest point in Hampi and offers breathtaking views of the surrounding landscape. It is also believed to be the place where Lord Rama met Hanuman in the Ramayana. The climb to the top can be steep, but the views are worth it.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lotus Mahal: This is a beautiful palace that was once used by the royal women of the Vijayanagara Empire. It is known for its unique architecture and beautiful lotus-shaped dome, which gives it its name.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">These are just a few of the many places to visit in Hampi. Whether you\'re interested in history, architecture, or just want to enjoy the natural beauty of the area, there is something for everyone in Hampi.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=26.923791999999988%2C75.82652100000001&z=18', '2023-05-05 14:12:59', '2023-05-05 14:12:59'),
(80, 'India', 'Karnataka', NULL, NULL, 'KOCHI TOURISTY PLACES', 'Kochi, Fort Kochi, Mattancherry Palace, Chinese fishing nets, Jewish Synagogue, Kerala cuisine, Backwaters of Kochi, St. Francis Church, Vasco da Gama Square, Marine Drive Kochi, Hill Palace Museum.', 'Welcome to Kochi, the Queen of the Arabian Sea, a vibrant city that is a perfect blend of old-world charm and modernity. Kochi, located on the southwest coast of India, has been a popular destination for travelers from all over the world.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Welcome to Kochi, the Queen of the Arabian Sea, a vibrant city that is a perfect blend of old-world charm and modernity. Kochi, located on the southwest coast of India, has been a popular destination for travelers from all over the world. Here are some of the must-visit touristy places in Kochi:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Fort Kochi - Built-in 1503 by the Portuguese, Fort Kochi is a popular tourist spot that showcases a mix of Portuguese, Dutch, and British architectural styles. It is also famous for its iconic Chinese fishing nets that line the shore.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mattancherry Palace - Also known as the Dutch Palace, this palace was built by the Portuguese and later renovated by the Dutch. It houses an impressive collection of murals and artifacts that depict the history and culture of Kochi.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">St. Francis Church - This is the oldest European church in India, built in 1503 by the Portuguese. It is famous for being the burial ground of Vasco da Gama, the Portuguese explorer who discovered the sea route to India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hill Palace Museum - Once the residence of the Maharaja of Kochi, the Hill Palace Museum is now a heritage museum that displays a vast collection of artifacts, paintings, and royal memorabilia.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jewish Synagogue - Located in the heart of the Jew Town, this synagogue is the oldest active synagogue in the Commonwealth of Nations. It is famous for its hand-painted Chinese tiles and Belgian chandeliers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kochi\'s rich history, diverse culture, and scenic beauty make it an exciting destination for travelers. Whether you want to explore the city\'s colonial past or indulge in the local cuisine, Kochi has something for everyone. Come and experience the magic of Kochi, where tradition meets modernity.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=9.931232799999988%2C76.26730409999998&z=18', '2023-05-05 14:15:00', '2023-05-05 14:15:00');
