(83, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'madurai', 'madurai', 'MADURAI TOURISTY PLACES', 'Temples, Culture, History, Meenakshi Temple, Thirumalai Nayak Palace, Koodal Azhagar Temple, Alagar Kovil, Gandhi Museum, Vandiyur Mariamman Teppakulam, Thiruparankundram Murugan Temple, Pazhamudhir Solai, Meenakshi Amman Temple, Architecture.', 'Madurai, also known as the \"Athens of the East,\" is a cultural and historical city in Tamil Nadu, India. Madurai is famous for its impressive temples, vibrant street markets, and rich culinary heritage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Madurai, also known as the \"Athens of the East,\" is a cultural and historical city in Tamil Nadu, India. Madurai is famous for its impressive temples, vibrant street markets, and rich culinary heritage.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Here are some of the must-visit tourist attractions in Madurai:</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Meenakshi Amman Temple: This ancient temple complex, dedicated to the goddess Meenakshi and her consort Lord Shiva, is the heart of Madurai. The temple\'s towering gopurams (gateway towers) adorned with intricate carvings and paintings, make it a magnificent sight to behold. The temple was built by the Pandyan dynasty in the 6th century, and it continues to be an important center of worship and pilgrimage.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thirumalai Nayakkar Mahal: This stunning palace was built by King Thirumalai Nayak in the 17th century. The palace\'s grand architecture is a blend of Dravidian and Islamic styles. It features massive pillars, exquisite stucco work, and a spacious courtyard. The palace is illuminated beautifully in the evenings, and visitors can enjoy a sound and light show that highlights its history.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gandhi Memorial Museum: Located in the heart of the city, this museum is dedicated to the life and legacy of Mahatma Gandhi. The museum features a vast collection of photographs, letters, and personal belongings of Gandhi. It also showcases the story of India\'s struggle for independence and Gandhi\'s role in it.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Madurai Food Tour: Madurai is known for its delectable cuisine, and a food tour is the best way to explore the city\'s culinary delights. Sample traditional dishes like dosa, idli, vada, and biryani, and taste the local specialty, jigarthanda - a refreshing drink made with milk, almond gum, and ice cream.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Madurai\'s rich cultural heritage, magnificent temples, and delicious cuisine make it a must-visit destination for travelers. Whether you\'re a history buff, a foodie, or simply seeking an authentic travel experience, Madurai has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=-7.058696526638575%2C113.39908500000001&z=9', '2023-05-06 06:00:43', '2023-05-06 06:00:43'),
(84, 'India', 'Kerala', 'Munnar', 'munnar', 'MUNNAR TOURISTY PLACES', 'Munnar, hill station, tea gardens, wildlife, Eravikulam National Park, Anamudi Peak, Mattupetty Dam, trekking, honeymoon destination, Kerala tourism.', 'Munnar, located in the southwestern state of Kerala, is a picturesque hill station surrounded by sprawling tea plantations, misty mountains, and lush forests. This idyllic town attracts thousands of visitors every year, who come to witness its breathtaking natural beauty, indulge in adventure activities, and experience the unique culture and cuisine of the region. Munnar is the perfect destination for those seeking a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of city life.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Munnar, located in the southwestern state of Kerala, is a picturesque hill station surrounded by sprawling tea plantations, misty mountains, and lush forests. This idyllic town attracts thousands of visitors every year, who come to witness its breathtaking natural beauty, indulge in adventure activities, and experience the unique culture and cuisine of the region. Munnar is the perfect destination for those seeking a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. Heres a guide to the must-visit tourist spots in Munnar, a picturesque hill station located in the Western Ghats of Kerala:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mattupetty Dam: Built in the 1940s, this dam is a popular tourist attraction that offers stunning views of the surrounding hills and valleys. Visitors can take a boat ride on the dam\'s reservoir and enjoy the serene surroundings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tea Museum: Munnar is known for its tea plantations, and the Tea Museum is a must-visit attraction for tea lovers. It showcases the history and evolution of tea production in the region and various tea-making techniques.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Eravikulam National Park: Located 15 km from Munnar, this national park is home to the endangered Nilgiri Tahr, a species of mountain goat. The park is also known for its stunning landscapes, including rolling hills, valleys, and waterfalls.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Top Station: This viewpoint offers breathtaking panoramic views of the Western Ghats and the Tamil Nadu plains. Visitors can take a scenic drive through tea plantations and forests to reach Top Station, which is located at an altitude of 1,700 meters.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kundala Lake: Surrounded by lush green hills and forests, Kundala Lake is a serene and picturesque spot that offers boating and other water activities. Visitors can also explore the nearby Aruvikkad Waterfall and the famous Neela Kurinji flowers, which bloom once in 12 years.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Anamudi Peak: Located within the Eravikulam National Park, Anamudi Peak is the highest peak in South India, standing at an elevation of 2,695 meters. Visitors can go on a trek to the summit and enjoy stunning views of the surrounding hills and valleys.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Attukad Waterfall: This scenic waterfall is located between Munnar and Pallivasal and offers a great spot for a picnic or a leisurely hike. The waterfall is surrounded by lush green hills and tea plantations, making it a popular spot for photography.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overall, Munnar offers a perfect blend of natural beauty, adventure, and relaxation, making it a must-visit destination for travelers who seek a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of city life.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=10.080649882538486%2C77.06417789999999&z=14', '2023-05-06 06:02:46', '2023-05-06 06:02:46'),
(85, 'India', 'Karnataka', 'Mysore', 'mysore', 'MYSORE TOURISTY PLACES', 'Mysore Palace, Chamundi Hill, Brindavan Gardens, St. Philomena\'s Church, Mysore Zoo, Jaganmohan Palace, Karanji Lake, Mysore Sandalwood Oil, Dasara festival, Srirangapatna, Tipu Sultan.', 'Mysore, a city rich in history and culture, is located in the southern state of Karnataka in India. Known as the \"City of Palaces\", Mysore offers a wide range of attractions, from palaces and temples to natural wonders and markets.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mysore, a city rich in history and culture, is located in the southern state of Karnataka in India. Known as the \"City of Palaces\", Mysore offers a wide range of attractions, from palaces and temples to natural wonders and markets. Let\'s explore some of the must-visit places in Mysore:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mysore Palace: Built in the 14th century, this palace is the biggest attraction in Mysore. It was built by the Wodeyar dynasty and is an excellent example of Indo-Saracenic architecture. The palace is a visual delight, especially during the Dussehra festival when it is illuminated with thousands of lights.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Chamundi Hill: Located on the outskirts of Mysore, Chamundi Hill is home to the famous Chamundeshwari Temple, which is dedicated to the goddess Chamundeshwari. The hill also offers breathtaking views of the city.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Brindavan Gardens: Located near the KRS Dam, Brindavan Gardens is a popular spot for tourists to relax and unwind. The gardens are spread over 60 acres and are famous for their musical fountain show in the evenings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mysore Zoo: Spread over 157 acres, the Mysore Zoo is home to a wide variety of animals, including tigers, lions, elephants, and more. The zoo is known for its breeding programs and conservation efforts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">St. Philomena\'s Church: Built-in the Gothic style of architecture, this church is one of the largest churches in India. It was built in honor of St. Philomena, a 3rd-century saint from Greece.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mysore\'s rich cultural heritage and historical significance make it a must-visit destination in India. Whether you\'re interested in history, architecture, or nature, Mysore has something to offer for everyone. So, pack your bags and head to Mysore for an unforgettable experience!</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=12.310653505542408%2C76.63568979999997&z=12', '2023-05-06 06:05:24', '2023-05-06 06:05:24'),
(86, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'ooty', 'ooty', 'OOTY TOURIST PLACES', 'Ooty, Udhagamandalam, Nilgiris, Tamil Nadu, India, hill station, tea gardens, Doddabetta, Ooty Lake, Botanical Garden, Rose Garden, Pine Forest, Avalanche Lake, Mukurthi National Park, wildlife sanctuary, mountain trekking, toy train, tourism.', 'Nestled in the Nilgiri Hills of Tamil Nadu, Ooty is a picturesque hill station that offers a perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. It is known for its pleasant climate, lush greenery, and scenic beauty. Ooty has a rich history and culture that is reflected in its numerous tourist attractions.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nestled in the Nilgiri Hills of Tamil Nadu, Ooty is a picturesque hill station that offers a perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of city life. It is known for its pleasant climate, lush greenery, and scenic beauty. Ooty has a rich history and culture that is reflected in its numerous tourist attractions. In this article, we will explore some of the must-visit places in Ooty and their significance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most popular tourist attractions in Ooty is the Botanical Garden. Established in 1847, the garden was originally created to serve as a hub for introducing new plant species. Today, it is a popular spot for nature enthusiasts and tourists. The garden is home to several exotic plants and flowers, including rare and endangered species. Visitors can also take a leisurely walk around the garden or enjoy a picnic with family and friends.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Another popular attraction is the Ooty Lake, which was built in 1824 by John Sullivan, the then-British Collector of Coimbatore. The lake is surrounded by lush green hills and provides a serene atmosphere for visitors to relax and enjoy the scenic beauty. Boating facilities are available for visitors, making it an ideal spot for families to spend some quality time together.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">The Doddabetta Peak is the highest peak in the Nilgiri Hills and offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding hills and valleys. It is a popular spot for trekking and hiking enthusiasts, and visitors can also enjoy the picturesque views from the telescope house located at the top of the peak.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">The Government Rose Garden, also known as the Jayalalithaa Rose Garden, is another must-visit place in Ooty. It is the largest rose garden in India and home to over 20,000 varieties. The garden is spread over 10 acres and also has several other exotic flowers and plants.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Finally, the Toy Train Ride is a must-do activity for visitors to Ooty. The train journey takes you through the scenic beauty of the Nilgiri Hills and offers stunning views of the surrounding landscapes. The train ride is a popular activity for families and couples alike and is a great way to explore the natural beauty of Ooty.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Ooty is a charming hill station with a rich history and culture and several must-visit tourist attractions. Whether you are a nature lover, a history enthusiast, or just looking for a peaceful getaway, Ooty has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=11.411854227589023%2C76.69342159999998&z=13', '2023-05-06 06:09:10', '2023-05-06 06:09:10'),
(87, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Puducherry', 'puducherry', 'PUDUCHERRY TOURISTY PLACES', 'French colony, promenade beach, sri aurobindo ashram, paradise beach, arikamedu archaeological site, auroville, botanical garden, bharathi park, ousteri lake, manakula vinayagar temple', 'Puducherry, a French colonial town situated on the Bay of Bengal, offers a unique blend of cultures and traditions. A visit to Puducherry is incomplete without exploring the French Quarter, also known as White Town. The French Quarter boasts beautiful colonial-style buildings, quaint cafes, and chic boutiques. The area was built by the French during their colonial rule in India and showcases a perfect amalgamation of French and Tamil architecture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Puducherry, a French colonial town situated on the Bay of Bengal, offers a unique blend of cultures and traditions. A visit to Puducherry is incomplete without exploring the French Quarter, also known as White Town. The French Quarter boasts beautiful colonial-style buildings, quaint cafes, and chic boutiques. The area was built by the French during their colonial rule in India and showcases a perfect amalgamation of French and Tamil architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another must-visit attraction is Auroville, an experimental township founded in 1968. It was designed as a universal town where people from different countries, cultures, and beliefs could live together in peace and harmony. Auroville\'s famous Matrimandir is a spherical temple with a golden dome that symbolizes the birth of a new consciousness. It was designed by the French architect Roger Anger and is considered a modern marvel of architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Promenade Beach, also known as Rock Beach, is a popular tourist destination in Puducherry. It stretches over 1.2 km and is known for its vibrant ambiance and scenic views. The beachfront is lined with statues, cafes, and street vendors, making it the perfect spot for a leisurely stroll.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Sri Aurobindo Ashram is another significant attraction in Puducherry. The ashram was founded by Sri Aurobindo and his spiritual collaborator, the Mother, in 1926. It is a hub of spirituality and self-discovery and attracts visitors from across the world who seek spiritual solace and inner peace.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Puducherry is also home to some of the best cafes and restaurants in the region, serving delicious French and Tamil cuisine. The quaint French Quarter has cafes and restaurants offering a delightful culinary experience.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Puducherry is a charming destination that offers a unique blend of history, culture, and spirituality. It is a perfect place to unwind and reconnect with oneself amidst its tranquil surroundings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=11.941591500000017%2C79.8083133&z=13', '2023-05-06 06:12:19', '2023-05-06 06:13:23'),
(88, 'India', 'Uttarakhand', NULL, NULL, 'RISHIKESH TOURISTY PLACES', 'Rishikesh tourism, yoga, adventure sports, Ganges river, spirituality, ancient temples, Beatles Ashram, Triveni Ghat, Neer Garh waterfall, Lakshman Jhula, Ram Jhula, Parmarth Niketan Ashram.', 'Nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas, Rishikesh is a city that holds great spiritual significance for Hindus. The city is situated on the banks of the holy river Ganga and is home to several ancient temples, ashrams, and ghats.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas, Rishikesh is a city that holds great spiritual significance for Hindus. The city is situated on the banks of the holy river Ganga and is home to several ancient temples, ashrams, and ghats.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most significant places in Rishikesh is the Triveni Ghat, where the three holy rivers of Ganga, Yamuna, and Saraswati converge. It is believed that taking a dip in the Triveni Ghat will wash away all sins and provide moksha or liberation from the cycle of birth and death.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Parmarth Niketan is another important ashram in Rishikesh, which was established by Swami Shukdevanandji Maharaj in 1942. The ashram is known for its yoga and meditation programs, and visitors can attend various workshops and classes.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Neelkanth Mahadev Temple is also a must-visit place in Rishikesh. The temple is situated at a height of 1,330 meters and is dedicated to Lord Shiva. It is believed that Lord Shiva consumed poison at this spot, which turned his throat blue, hence the name Neelkanth.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Beatles Ashram, also known as the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi Ashram, is a popular tourist spot in Rishikesh. The ashram was made famous by the Beatles, who visited it in 1968 to learn transcendental meditation from Maharishi Mahesh Yogi.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Rishikesh is also known as the \'Yoga Capital of the World\' and attracts thousands of visitors from around the globe every year to attend various yoga and meditation retreats.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Rishikesh is a city that offers a unique blend of spirituality, adventure, and tranquility. Its temples, ashrams, and ghats hold great significance in Hindu mythology and offer visitors an opportunity to experience the rich cultural heritage of India. Whether you are seeking spiritual solace or adventure sports, Rishikesh has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=30.087690132289637%2C78.27060874999998&z=12', '2023-05-06 06:23:03', '2023-05-06 06:23:03'),
(89, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Shimla', 'shimla', 'SHIMLA TOURISTY PLACES', 'Shimla, Himachal Pradesh, India, tourist attractions, travel guide, hill stations, scenic beauty, adventure sports, trekking, skiing, honeymoon destination, colonial architecture, shopping, handicrafts.', 'Shimla, the capital city of the northern Indian state of Himachal Pradesh, is a popular hill station nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas. It was once the summer capital of British India and has since then been a favorite destination among travelers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shimla, the capital city of the northern Indian state of Himachal Pradesh, is a popular hill station nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas. It was once the summer capital of British India and has since then been a favorite destination among travelers. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Shimla:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Ridge: This open space located in the heart of Shimla is famous for its stunning views of the surrounding hills and colonial-era buildings. The Ridge is a popular spot for leisurely walks, picnics, and cultural events.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Christ Church: Built-in 1857, Christ Church is one of the oldest churches in northern India. Its stained-glass windows, Gothic architecture, and peaceful ambiance make it a must-visit attraction in Shimla.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mall Road: This bustling street is lined with shops, restaurants, and cafes and is a hub of activity in Shimla. Visitors can stroll down Mall Road, shop for souvenirs, and enjoy local delicacies.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jakhu Hill: At a height of 2,455 meters, Jakhu Hill offers panoramic views of Shimla and the surrounding mountains. It is also home to a famous Hanuman temple, which attracts a large number of devotees every day.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shimla State Museum: The museum, established in 1974, showcases the rich cultural heritage of Himachal Pradesh. It houses a collection of ancient artifacts, paintings, sculptures, and handicrafts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">These attractions reflect the cultural and natural beauty of Shimla, and each one is unique in its own way. Visiting Shimla will give you a glimpse into the history and culture of India while allowing you to immerse yourself in the stunning natural surroundings of this charming hill station.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=31.078228251222363%2C77.15902125000001&z=13', '2023-05-06 06:25:07', '2023-05-06 06:25:07'),
(90, 'India', 'Uttar Pradesh', 'Varanasi', 'varanasi', 'VARANASI TOURIST PLACES', 'varanasi, india, hinduism, ganges, river, pilgrimage, culture, spirituality, history, temples, ghats, art, music, silk, handicrafts', 'Varanasi, also known as Banaras or Kashi, is a city in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is one of the world\'s oldest continuously inhabited cities and is considered one of the seven holiest cities in Hinduism. The city is situated on the banks of the river Ganges and is known for its spiritual and cultural significance. Varanasi is also known for its rich history, art, music, and literature. It attracts thousands of tourists from all over the world who come to experience the unique and vibrant culture of the city.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Varanasi, also known as Banaras or Kashi, is a city in the northern Indian state of Uttar Pradesh. It is one of the world\'s oldest continuously inhabited cities and is considered one of the seven holiest cities in Hinduism. The city is situated on the banks of the river Ganges and is known for its spiritual and cultural significance. Varanasi is also known for its rich history, art, music, and literature. It attracts thousands of tourists from all over the world who come to experience the unique and vibrant culture of the city.</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Kashi Vishwanath Temple - Located in the heart of Varanasi, the Kashi Vishwanath Temple is one of the most famous and sacred temples in India. The temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is believed to be one of the 12 Jyotirlingas. It is a must-visit for anyone interested in Hindu mythology and culture.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Dashashwamedh Ghat - Dashashwamedh Ghat is one of the most popular ghats in Varanasi and is famous for its evening aarti ceremony, where devotees offer prayers to the river Ganges. The ghat is also a great place to take a boat ride and enjoy the river and city views.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Sarnath - Sarnath is a famous Buddhist pilgrimage site located just a few kilometers from Varanasi. It is believed to be the place where Lord Buddha gave his first sermon after attaining enlightenment. The site houses a number of ancient Buddhist stupas and temples, including the famous Dhamek Stupa.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Banaras Hindu University - Banaras Hindu University is a renowned educational institution located in Varanasi. The university is known for its beautiful architecture, lush green campus, and excellent academic programs. It is a great place to visit for anyone interested in education and academia.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Ramnagar Fort - Ramnagar Fort is a historic fort located on the banks of the river Ganges. It was built in the 18th century by the kings of the Kashi Naresh dynasty and is known for its beautiful architecture and collection of ancient artifacts.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Manikarnika Ghat - Manikarnika Ghat is one of the most famous ghats in Varanasi and is known for its association with death and cremation rituals. It is believed that if a person is cremated here, they will attain salvation. The ghat is also a great place to observe the unique and vibrant culture of Varanasi.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Varanasi is a city with a rich cultural and spiritual heritage, and each of these places has its own unique history and significance. Visiting these places will give you a deeper understanding of the city\'s rich cultural heritage and spiritual significance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=25.3176452%2C82.9739144&z=13', '2023-05-06 06:29:44', '2023-05-06 06:29:44'),
(91, 'India', 'West Bengal', 'darjeeling', 'darjeeling', 'DARJEELING TOURISTY PLACES', 'Darjeeling, tea plantations, Himalayas, Tiger Hill, Batasia Loop, Peace Pagoda, Japanese Temple, Himalayan Mountaineering Institute, Padmaja Naidu Himalayan Zoological Park, Darjeeling Rangeet Valley Passenger Ropeway Cable Car, Kanchenjunga Mountain, Dar', 'Darjeeling, a picturesque hill station located in the Indian state of West Bengal, is a popular tourist destination known for its breathtaking views of the Himalayas, tea gardens, and colonial architecture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Darjeeling, a picturesque hill station located in the Indian state of West Bengal, is a popular tourist destination known for its breathtaking views of the Himalayas, tea gardens, and colonial architecture. Here are some of the must-visit places in Darjeeling:</span></p><p><br></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tiger Hill:</strong><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\"> A famous viewpoint that offers stunning sunrise views over the Kanchenjunga mountain range.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Batasia Loop: A railway loop that offers a 360-degree panoramic view of the hills and valleys of Darjeeling.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Darjeeling Himalayan Railway: A UNESCO World Heritage site, this railway is famous for its narrow-gauge toy train that runs from New Jalpaiguri to Darjeeling.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Padmaja Naidu Himalayan Zoological Park: Home to rare Himalayan species like snow leopards, red pandas, and Tibetan wolves.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Himalayan Mountaineering Institute: Founded by Tenzing Norgay, this institute offers courses in mountaineering and displays equipment used in famous mountaineering expeditions.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Happy Valley Tea Estate: A sprawling tea garden where visitors can see the tea-making process and sample different varieties of tea.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Japanese Peace Pagoda: Built by Japanese monks, this pagoda is a symbol of peace and offers a serene view of the surrounding mountains.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ghoom Monastery: One of the oldest monasteries in Darjeeling, it houses a 15-foot high statue of Maitreya Buddha.</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">These places in Darjeeling offer a glimpse into the history, culture, and natural beauty of the region. A visit to Darjeeling is a unique experience that will leave you with memories for a lifetime.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=27.04102180000002%2C88.2662745&z=13', '2023-05-06 06:34:46', '2023-05-06 06:35:35'),
(92, 'India', 'Karnataka', 'Madikeri', 'madikeri', 'Madikeri Touristy Places', 'Madikeri, Coorg, Karnataka, India, hill station, coffee plantations, Raja\'s Seat, Abbey Falls, Omkareshwara Temple, Dubare Elephant Camp, Talakaveri Wildlife Sanctuary.', 'Madikeri, a picturesque hill station located in the Western Ghats of Karnataka, is a popular tourist destination known for its lush greenery, rolling hills, and coffee plantations. The town is rich in history and culture, and there are several interesting places to visit that showcase its heritage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Madikeri, a picturesque hill station located in the Western Ghats of Karnataka, is a popular tourist destination known for its lush greenery, rolling hills, and coffee plantations. The town is rich in history and culture, and there are several interesting places to visit that showcase its heritage.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most famous tourist attractions in Madikeri is the Madikeri Fort, built by Mudduraja in the 17th century. The fort was later rebuilt by Tipu Sultan, and it served as an important military center during the reign of the British. Today, the fort houses a museum that showcases the history and culture of the region.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another must-visit attraction is the Raja\'s Seat, a beautiful garden that was once the favorite spot of the kings of Kodagu. The garden offers a stunning panoramic view of the surrounding hills and valleys and is the perfect place to relax and soak in the natural beauty of the area.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">For those interested in spirituality and religion, the Omkareshwara Temple is a must-visit. Built in the 19th century, the temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and features a unique blend of Gothic and Islamic architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nature lovers will enjoy a visit to Abbey Falls, located just a few kilometers from Madikeri. The waterfall is surrounded by lush greenery and is a popular spot for picnics and trekking.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overall, Madikeri is a beautiful and peaceful hill station that offers something for everyone. Its rich history, natural beauty, and cultural heritage make it a must-visit destination in Karnataka.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=12.43142902948461%2C75.73486990000002&z=14', '2023-05-06 08:54:15', '2023-05-06 08:54:15'),
(93, 'India', 'Gujrat', 'ahemdabad', 'ahemdabad', 'Ahmedabad Tourist Places', 'Ahmedabad, also known as Amdavad, is a city in the western Indian state of Gujarat. It is a city steeped in history, culture, and tradition.', 'Ahmedabad, also known as Amdavad, is a city in the western Indian state of Gujarat. It is a city steeped in history, culture, and tradition.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ahmedabad, also known as Amdavad, is a city in the western Indian state of Gujarat. It is a city steeped in history, culture, and tradition. Here are some of the top tourist attractions that you should definitely visit when you\'re in Ahmedabad:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sabarmati Ashram: The ashram is one of the most visited places in Ahmedabad as it was home to the Father of the Nation, Mahatma Gandhi, during the Indian independence movement. It was from here that Gandhi launched his famous Dandi March.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Jama Masjid: The mosque was built in 1424 and is one of the largest mosques in India. The architecture is a perfect blend of Hindu and Islamic styles.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kankaria Lake: This is a man-made lake built in 1451 by Sultan Qutb-ud-Din. It is a popular spot for boating, picnics, and cultural programs.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sidi Saiyyed Mosque: This mosque is famous for its intricate stone latticework on the windows, which is a masterpiece of Indo-Islamic architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bhadra Fort and Teen Darwaza: Built-in the 15th century, the fort was used as the royal court during the reign of the Maratha Empire. The Teen Darwaza is a triple-arched gateway that leads to the fort.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Adalaj Stepwell: The stepwell was built in 1499 and is a perfect example of Indo-Islamic architecture. The stepwell is intricately carved and has five stories.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Calico Museum of Textiles: The museum houses one of the finest collections of textiles in India. The collection includes rare and antique textiles from all over India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sarkhej Roza: This is a complex of tombs, mosques, and palaces built-in 1451. It is a fine example of Indo-Islamic architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ahmedabad is a city that is steeped in history, culture, and tradition. There is so much to see and do here that you will never run out of things to explore. So, make sure to add Ahmedabad to your travel bucket list and experience the charm and magic of this city for yourself!</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1jBRh2yzA1mu3jvlLH4E6YqWPerk&hl=en&ll=23.022505%2C72.57136209999999&z=14', '2023-05-06 09:05:09', '2023-05-06 09:05:09'),
(94, 'India', 'Uttarakhand', 'auli', 'auli', 'Auli Touristy Places', 'Auli\'s popular attractions include the Auli Artificial Lake, the Auli Ropeway, the Nanda Devi National Park, the Chenab Lake, the Trishul Peak, the Joshimath Temple, and the Gurso Bugyal Trek', 'Auli is a picturesque hill station situated in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. It is known for its scenic beauty and is a popular destination among adventure seekers and nature lovers.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Auli is a picturesque hill station situated in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. It is known for its scenic beauty and is a popular destination among adventure seekers and nature lovers. Here are some of the must-visit touristy places in Auli.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Auli Artificial Lake: This is a man-made lake situated in Auli. It was built to provide artificial snow for skiing during the winter months. Today, it is a popular tourist attraction where visitors can enjoy boating and take in the stunning views of the surrounding mountains.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gurso Bugyal: It is a beautiful meadow located at an altitude of 3056 meters. It is surrounded by coniferous trees and provides a panoramic view of the Himalayas. It is an ideal place for nature walks and trekking.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Joshimath: It is a small town located near Auli. It is famous for its ancient temples and is the winter seat of the famous Badrinath temple. It is also a base for trekking and skiing expeditions.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nanda Devi National Park: It is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a biosphere reserve located near Auli. It is home to several endangered species of flora and fauna, including the elusive snow leopard. Visitors can go on wildlife safaris and trekking expeditions in the park.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Auli Ropeway: It is one of the longest ropeways in Asia and provides breathtaking views of the surrounding mountains. It is a popular attraction among tourists who want to enjoy panoramic views of the Himalayas.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Auli is a paradise for nature lovers and adventure seekers. With its stunning natural beauty and plethora of tourist attractions, it is a must-visit destination for anyone looking for an escape from the hustle and bustle of city life.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=30.529865779884283%2C79.56491899999999&z=15', '2023-05-06 09:07:37', '2023-05-06 09:07:37');
