(95, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Dalhousie', 'dalhousie', 'Dalhousie Touristy Places', 'Hills, Scenic beauty, Colonial architecture, Temples, Churches, Trekking, Adventure sports, Khajjiar, Nature walks, Dainkund Peak, Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary, Panchpula, Satdhara Falls, Chamera Lake, Shopping, Handicrafts, Local cuisine.', 'Dalhousie, located in the picturesque state of Himachal Pradesh, is a small and charming hill station that attracts a large number of tourists every year. The town is known for its scenic beauty, serene environment, and colonial architecture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dalhousie, located in the picturesque state of Himachal Pradesh, is a small and charming hill station that attracts a large number of tourists every year. The town is known for its scenic beauty, serene environment, and colonial architecture. Let\'s take a look at some of the top tourist places in Dalhousie:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Khajjiar - Often referred to as the \"Mini Switzerland of India,\" Khajjiar is a beautiful meadow surrounded by dense forests. The place is perfect for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and photographers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dainkund Peak - Dainkund Peak is the highest peak in Dalhousie and offers breathtaking views of the surrounding valleys and mountains. It is a must-visit destination for trekkers and nature enthusiasts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary - Spread over an area of 30.69 square kilometers, Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary is home to a variety of flora and fauna. It is an ideal destination for wildlife enthusiasts and bird watchers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Satdhara Falls - Satdhara Falls is a scenic waterfall located at a distance of 4 kilometers from Dalhousie. The waterfall is famous for its seven streams and is considered to have therapeutic properties.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Chamera Lake - Chamera Lake is a popular destination for water sports activities like boating, fishing, and kayaking. The lake is surrounded by lush green hills and is an ideal spot for picnics and family outings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dalhousie was named after Lord Dalhousie, who was the British Governor-General of India from 1848 to 1856. The town was established by the British in the mid-19th century as a summer retreat for their troops and officials. Today, it is a popular tourist destination known for its natural beauty, pleasant weather, and colonial charm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you\'re planning a trip to Dalhousie, make sure to include these top tourist places in your itinerary. You\'ll be amazed by the scenic beauty and serenity of this charming hill station.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=32.53873850000002%2C75.97099779999999&z=15', '2023-05-06 09:09:26', '2023-05-06 09:09:26'),
(96, 'India', 'Uttarakhand', 'dehradun', 'dehradun', 'Dehradun Tourist Places', 'Dehradun, Uttarakhand, tourism, travel, nature, adventure, history, culture, mountains, Himalayas, sightseeing', 'Dehradun, the capital city of Uttarakhand, is a picturesque hill station located in the foothills of the Himalayas. It is known for its scenic beauty, pleasant weather, and natural wonders.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dehradun, the capital city of Uttarakhand, is a picturesque hill station located in the foothills of the Himalayas. It is known for its scenic beauty, pleasant weather, and natural wonders. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Dehradun:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Robber\'s Cave: Also known as Gucchu Pani, it is a natural cave formation that is famous for its unique structure and underground river.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sahastradhara: It is a popular tourist spot known for its natural beauty and therapeutic value. The name Sahastradhara means \"thousand-fold spring\" and refers to the abundance of water in the area.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Forest Research Institute: It is one of the oldest institutes of its kind in the country and is known for its beautiful architecture, lush green surroundings, and research on forestry and wood sciences.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tapkeshwar Temple: This ancient temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is known for its natural water springs and serene environment.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Malsi Deer Park: It is a zoological park and a popular picnic spot that is home to various species of deer, peacocks, and other animals.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mindrolling Monastery: It is one of the largest Buddhist learning centers in India and is known for its beautiful architecture and peaceful ambiance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Clock Tower: It is a landmark of Dehradun and is located in the heart of the city. The tower is surrounded by bustling markets and is a popular shopping destination for locals and tourists alike.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dehradun offers a perfect blend of natural beauty, historical significance, and modern amenities. It is a must-visit destination for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and those seeking a peaceful retreat amidst the hills. A trip to Dehradun is sure to leave you with unforgettable memories that you will cherish for a lifetime.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=30.31649450000002%2C78.03219179999998&z=15', '2023-05-06 12:14:50', '2023-05-06 12:14:50'),
(97, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Dharamsala', 'dharamsala', 'Dharamshala Tourist Places', 'Dharamshala, Himachal Pradesh, India, travel, tourism, mountains, Himalayas, culture, history, spirituality, adventure, trekking, hiking, Tibetan, Buddhism, Dalai Lama, McLeod Ganj, Kangra Valley.', 'Dharamshala, a quaint town in the state of Himachal Pradesh, is one of the most popular tourist destinations in India', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dharamshala, a quaint town in the state of Himachal Pradesh, is one of the most popular tourist destinations in India. Here are some of the top touristy places in Dharamshala:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dalai Lama Temple Complex: The Dalai Lama Temple Complex, also known as the Tsuglagkhang Complex, is a spiritual and cultural center for the Tibetan community. It houses the residence of the 14th Dalai Lama, a museum, a library, and several temples.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bhagsu Waterfall: Located about 2 km from the town of McLeod Ganj, the Bhagsu Waterfall is a popular tourist spot. The waterfall cascades down from a height of 30 feet and is surrounded by lush greenery.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Namgyal Monastery: The Namgyal Monastery is the largest Tibetan monastery outside of Tibet. It is a popular tourist spot and a center for Buddhist learning.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Triund Trek: The Triund Trek is a popular trekking trail in Dharamshala. The trek takes you through scenic forests and hills, and offers stunning views of the Dhauladhar range.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kangra Fort: The Kangra Fort is a historic fort located about 20 km from Dharamshala. The fort was built by the Katoch dynasty in the 4th century and was later captured by the Mughals, the Sikhs, and the British.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dharamkot: Dharamkot is a small village located about 3 km from McLeod Ganj. The village is known for its scenic beauty, peaceful atmosphere, and vibrant culture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dharamshala is a perfect destination for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and those interested in Tibetan culture and spirituality. With its stunning landscapes, vibrant culture, and peaceful atmosphere, Dharamshala is a must-visit destination in India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=32.216779990503646%2C76.31916524999998&z=14', '2023-05-06 12:16:45', '2023-05-06 12:16:45'),
(98, 'India', 'Goa', NULL, NULL, 'Goa Tourist Places', 'beaches, nightlife, water sports, churches, Portuguese architecture, seafood, markets, coconut groves, forts, yoga, music festivals.', 'Goa is a coastal state located in western India and is known for its pristine beaches, vibrant nightlife, and rich cultural heritage', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Goa is a coastal state located in western India and is known for its pristine beaches, vibrant nightlife, and rich cultural heritage. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Goa:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Beaches: Goa is famous for its beautiful beaches, such as Baga Beach, Calangute Beach, and Anjuna Beach. These beaches offer a wide range of activities, including sunbathing, swimming, and water sports.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Forts: There are several forts in Goa that were built by the Portuguese during their rule, such as Aguada Fort, Chapora Fort, and Reis Magos Fort. These forts provide a glimpse into the state\'s history and offer panoramic views of the coastline.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Churches: Goa is home to several historic churches, such as the Basilica of Bom Jesus, which is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Other notable churches include the Se Cathedral, the Church of Our Lady of the Immaculate Conception, and the Church of St. Francis of Assisi.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Wildlife Sanctuaries: Goa is also home to several wildlife sanctuaries, such as the Bondla Wildlife Sanctuary and the Cotigao Wildlife Sanctuary. These sanctuaries are home to a variety of flora and fauna and offer visitors a chance to experience Goa\'s natural beauty.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Waterfalls: Dudhsagar Waterfall is one of the most popular tourist attractions in Goa. It is located on the Mandovi River and is one of the highest waterfalls in India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Goa\'s unique blend of culture, history, and natural beauty make it a must-visit destination for any traveler. Whether you want to relax on the beach, explore the state\'s history and culture, or experience its natural wonders, Goa has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=15.350216329656147%2C74.0066944&z=9', '2023-05-06 12:18:56', '2023-05-06 12:18:56'),
(99, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Khajjiar', 'khajjiar', 'Khajjiar Touristy Places', 'Himalayan mountains, lush green landscapes, Khajjiar Lake, Khajji Nag Temple, Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary, Dhauladhar Range, Kailash Village, Panch Pandav Tree, Khajjiar Trek, Paragliding.', 'Nestled in the lap of the Himalayas, Khajjiar is a small hill station in Himachal Pradesh known for its picturesque beauty and lush green landscapes. One of the most popular tourist destinations in the state, Khajjiar is also known as \"Mini Switzerland of India\" due to its scenic beauty and serene ambiance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nestled in the lap of the Himalayas, Khajjiar is a small hill station in Himachal Pradesh known for its picturesque beauty and lush green landscapes. One of the most popular tourist destinations in the state, Khajjiar is also known as \"Mini Switzerland of India\" due to its scenic beauty and serene ambiance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Khajjiar is famous for its natural beauty, with the most popular attraction being the Khajjiar Lake, which is surrounded by lush green forests and is a popular spot for boating. Another major attraction is the Khajji Nag Temple, which was built in the 12th century and is dedicated to Lord Shiva.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Kailash Viewpoint is another popular spot that offers panoramic views of the surrounding hills and valleys. It is a great place to catch a sunrise or sunset and enjoy the natural beauty of the region. The Kalatop Wildlife Sanctuary is also a must-visit, offering a chance to witness the diverse flora and fauna of the region.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Khajjiar is also known for its adventure activities such as paragliding, trekking, and horse riding. Adventure enthusiasts can indulge in these activities and experience the thrill of being amidst nature.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overall, Khajjiar is a destination that offers a perfect blend of natural beauty, adventure, and spiritualism. It is a place that will leave you awestruck with its sheer magnificence and charm.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, if you are looking for a break from the hustle and bustle of city life and want to explore the beauty of nature, Khajjiar should definitely be on your bucket list.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=32.555794999999996%2C76.06558339999998&z=9', '2023-05-06 12:21:23', '2023-05-06 12:22:13'),
(100, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'kodaikanal', 'kodaikanal', 'Kodaikanal Touristy Places', 'Lakes, waterfalls, viewpoints, Coaker\'s Walk, Bryant Park, Kodai Lake, Pillar Rocks, Berijam Lake, Dolphin\'s Nose, Pine forests, Green Valley View, Kurinji Andavar Temple, Guna Caves, Bear Shola Falls, Silver Cascade Falls, trekking, boating, nature walks', 'Nestled in the Palani Hills of Tamil Nadu, Kodaikanal is a charming hill station that boasts of breathtaking natural beauty and a serene ambiance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nestled in the Palani Hills of Tamil Nadu, Kodaikanal is a charming hill station that boasts of breathtaking natural beauty and a serene ambiance. Here are some of the must-visit tourist spots in Kodaikanal:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kodai Lake: Built-in 1863, this man-made lake is the heart of Kodaikanal and offers stunning views of the surrounding hills. Visitors can take a boat ride, cycling, or simply stroll along the picturesque lake.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Coaker\'s Walk: Named after Lt. Coaker, this scenic walkway provides a panoramic view of the valley and the distant hills. It is a perfect spot for nature lovers and photographers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bryant Park: Spread over 20 acres, Bryant Park is a beautifully landscaped garden that houses a wide variety of flowers, trees, and shrubs. Visitors can relax on the lush lawns, stroll, or enjoy a picnic amidst the serene surroundings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pillar Rocks: These giant rock pillars are a sight to behold and offer a stunning view of the surrounding landscape. Visitors can also explore the nearby caves and waterfalls.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bear Shola Falls: This picturesque waterfall is nestled amidst the dense forest and is a popular spot for trekking and picnicking.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kodaikanal has a rich history and was established as a hill station by the British in the 19th century. Today, it is a popular tourist destination and attracts visitors from all over the world. The town is also known for its delicious local cuisine and handmade chocolates.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Whether you\'re a nature lover, an adventure seeker or simply looking for a relaxing getaway, Kodaikanal has something for everyone. So pack your bags and head to this picturesque hill station for an unforgettable vacation!</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=10.235152209506257%2C77.49687199999998&z=13', '2023-05-06 12:24:32', '2023-05-06 12:27:56'),
(101, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Kullu', 'kullu', 'Kullu Tourist Places', 'Adventure sports, natural beauty, temples, festivals, hill stations, scenic drives, camping, trekking, skiing, river rafting, paragliding, apple orchards, hot springs, traditional handicrafts.', 'Kullu is a beautiful valley located in the state of Himachal Pradesh in northern India. It is a popular destination among tourists and adventure enthusiasts because of its scenic beauty, cultural significance, and outdoor activities.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kullu is a beautiful valley located in the state of Himachal Pradesh in northern India. It is a popular destination among tourists and adventure enthusiasts because of its scenic beauty, cultural significance, and outdoor activities. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Kullu:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Raghunath Temple: Built in the 17th century, the Raghunath Temple is one of the most famous temples in Kullu. It is dedicated to Lord Rama and is believed to be the protector of the valley.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bijli Mahadev Temple: The Bijli Mahadev Temple is located on top of a hill and is dedicated to Lord Shiva. The temple has a 60-feet tall staff that attracts lightning strikes, and it is believed that the priest of the temple uses a special technique to revive the Shiva Lingam after every lightning strike.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Great Himalayan National Park: The Great Himalayan National Park is a UNESCO World Heritage site and is home to a wide variety of flora and fauna. The park is known for its trekking routes and is a paradise for adventure enthusiasts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kullu Dussehra: Kullu Dussehra is one of the most popular festivals in Kullu and is celebrated with great enthusiasm. The festival lasts for seven days and is a celebration of Lord Raghunath.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kasol: Kasol is a small village located in the Parvati Valley and is known for its scenic beauty, trekking routes, and hippie culture. It is a popular destination among backpackers and adventure enthusiasts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Solang Valley: The Solang Valley is a beautiful valley located between Beas Kund and Solang village. It is known for its adventure activities such as skiing, paragliding, and zorbing.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kullu is a must-visit destination for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and those interested in cultural tourism. The scenic beauty of the valley, coupled with its rich culture and history, makes it a unique and unforgettable experience for visitors.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=31.95458713516792%2C77.11129239999998&z=14', '2023-05-06 12:29:33', '2023-05-06 12:29:33'),
(102, 'India', 'Ladakh', NULL, NULL, 'Ladakh Tourist Places', 'Ladakh tourism, Ladakh sightseeing, Places to visit in Ladakh, Ladakh culture, Himalayan tourism, Leh-Ladakh tourism, Zanskar valley tourism, Nubra valley tourism, Pangong Tso Lake tourism, Khardung La pass tourism, Monasteries in Ladakh, Trekking in Lada', 'Ladakh, also known as the land of high passes, is a region in the Indian state of Jammu and Kashmir that is renowned for its stunning natural beauty, rich culture, and adventurous landscapes. It is home to numerous picturesque villages, ancient monasteries, pristine lakes, and lofty mountain ranges.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ladakh, also known as the land of high passes, is a region in the Indian state of Jammu and Kashmir that is renowned for its stunning natural beauty, rich culture, and adventurous landscapes. It is home to numerous picturesque villages, ancient monasteries, pristine lakes, and lofty mountain ranges. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Ladakh:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pangong Tso Lake: One of the most popular tourist spots in Ladakh, the Pangong Tso Lake is a breathtakingly beautiful high-altitude lake that is surrounded by rugged mountains. The lake changes its color throughout the day, ranging from shades of blue, green, and turquoise, making it a photographer\'s delight.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Leh Palace: The Leh Palace is a magnificent nine-storey palace that was built in the 17th century by King Sengge Namgyal. It offers panoramic views of the entire Leh town and the surrounding snow-capped mountains.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shanti Stupa: The Shanti Stupa is a white-domed Buddhist stupa that was built by a Japanese Buddhist monk to promote world peace. It is situated on a hilltop in Chanspa, offering stunning views of the Leh valley.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nubra Valley: Located in the northeastern part of Ladakh, the Nubra Valley is known for its breathtaking natural beauty, scenic vistas, and ancient monasteries. It is also famous for its sand dunes and the unique double-humped Bactrian camels.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Magnetic Hill: The Magnetic Hill is a gravity hill located near Leh, where vehicles appear to defy gravity and move uphill without any power. It is a popular spot among tourists and is believed to have magnetic properties that attract cars to move uphill.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hemis Monastery: The Hemis Monastery is the largest and wealthiest monastery in Ladakh, known for its ancient architecture, rich cultural heritage, and exquisite paintings and artifacts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Khardung La Pass: The Khardung La Pass is one of the highest motorable passes in the world, located at an altitude of 5,359 meters above sea level. It offers breathtaking views of the Karakoram and Zanskar ranges.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tso Moriri Lake: Tso Moriri Lake is a pristine high-altitude lake located in the Changthang region of Ladakh. It is known for its crystal clear blue waters, rugged mountain ranges, and diverse wildlife.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Zanskar Valley: The Zanskar Valley is a remote and isolated valley located in the eastern part of Ladakh. It is known for its stunning natural beauty, snow-capped peaks, ancient monasteries, and traditional way of life.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kargil War Memorial: The Kargil War Memorial is a tribute to the soldiers who fought and sacrificed their lives during the Kargil War in 1999. It is located in Drass, which is the second coldest inhabited place in the world.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ladakh is a unique destination that offers a perfect blend of natural beauty, adventure, and spirituality. Whether you are a nature lover, adventure enthusiast, or a spiritual seeker, Ladakh has something to offer for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=34.2268475%2C77.5619419&z=14', '2023-05-12 10:52:51', '2023-05-12 10:52:51'),
(103, 'India', 'Ladakh', 'leh', 'leh', 'Leh Tourist Places', 'Leh tourism, Leh sightseeing, Places to visit in Leh, Leh culture, Himalayan tourism, Ladakh tourism, Zanskar valley tourism, Nubra valley tourism, Pangong Tso Lake tourism.', 'Leh, the land of high passes, is a mesmerizing destination located in the northernmost region of India. It offers a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural richness, and adventure.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Leh, the land of high passes, is a mesmerizing destination located in the northernmost region of India. It offers a unique blend of natural beauty, cultural richness, and adventure. Here are some of the top tourist attractions that you should visit during your trip to Leh:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Leh Palace: Built in the 17th century, the Leh Palace is a towering nine-story building that offers a panoramic view of the city. It was built by King Sengge Namgyal and is a fine example of medieval Tibetan architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Magnetic Hill: One of the most intriguing destinations in Leh, Magnetic Hill is a natural wonder where you can experience a phenomenon of the magnetic force. It is believed that if you park your vehicle at the base of the hill, it will move up the hill on its own.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shanti Stupa: The white-domed Shanti Stupa is a Buddhist monument that was built by the Japanese in 1991 to promote world peace. It offers a breathtaking view of Leh and the surrounding mountains.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nubra Valley: Located about 150 km from Leh, Nubra Valley is a high-altitude desert that is famous for its sand dunes, double-humped camels, and ancient monasteries.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pangong Tso Lake: This magnificent lake is situated at a height of 14,270 feet and is one of the highest saltwater lakes in the world. Its crystal-clear blue waters surrounded by snow-capped mountains make for a breathtaking view.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Khardung La Pass: At an altitude of 18,379 feet, Khardung La Pass is one of the highest motorable roads in the world. It offers a thrilling adventure for adventure enthusiasts and also provides stunning views of the surrounding mountains.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hemis National Park: Home to the elusive snow leopard, Hemis National Park is a must-visit for wildlife enthusiasts. The park is also home to other rare and endangered species such as the Tibetan wolf and the Eurasian brown bear.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Leh is truly a paradise on earth that offers an unforgettable experience to its visitors. Whether you are an adventure enthusiast, a nature lover, or a cultural enthusiast, Leh has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=34.152586400000004%2C77.57705349999998&z=14', '2023-05-12 10:55:02', '2023-05-12 10:55:02'),
(104, 'India', 'Maharashtra', 'lonavala', 'lonavala', 'Lonavala Tourist Places', 'Lonavala tourism, Lonavala sightseeing, Places to visit in Lonavala, Lonavala hill stations, Western Ghats tourism, Lonavala caves, Lonavala waterfalls, Adventure tourism in Lonavala, Lonavala trekking, Lonavala camping.', 'Lonavala is a popular hill station located in the Western Ghats of Maharashtra. It is a beautiful weekend getaway from Mumbai and Pune, attracting tourists throughout the year.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lonavala is a popular hill station located in the Western Ghats of Maharashtra. It is a beautiful weekend getaway from Mumbai and Pune, attracting tourists throughout the year. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Lonavala:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bhushi Dam: This popular tourist spot is a perfect place to spend some time with family and friends. The dam is surrounded by lush greenery and provides a scenic view of the Sahyadri mountains.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tiger\'s Leap: It is a popular vantage point in Lonavala that offers a panoramic view of the surrounding hills and valleys. The spot gets its name due to its resemblance to a tiger leaping into the valley.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lonavala Lake: The beautiful lake is surrounded by hills and provides a serene and peaceful atmosphere. It is a great place for picnics and boat rides.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Karla Caves: These ancient rock-cut Buddhist caves date back to the 2nd century BC and are an important historical and religious site in the area.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Rajmachi Fort: This historical fort is located atop a hill and provides a great view of the surrounding valleys. It was built by Shivaji in the 17th century and played an important role in the Maratha Empire.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Wax Museum: The Wax Museum in Lonavala is a popular tourist attraction that showcases life-size wax statues of famous personalities.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lonavala is a great place to escape the hustle and bustle of the city and enjoy the scenic beauty of the Western Ghats. Whether you are looking for adventure or a peaceful retreat, Lonavala has something to offer for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=18.755723699999987%2C73.4090757&z=14', '2023-05-12 10:57:25', '2023-05-12 10:59:19'),
(105, 'India', 'Himachal Pradesh', 'Mc Leod Ganj', 'mc-leod-ganj', 'McLeod Ganj Tourist Places', 'McLeod Ganj tourism, McLeod Ganj sightseeing, Places to visit in McLeod Ganj, Tibetan culture, Himalayan tourism, Dharamshala tourism, Bhagsu waterfall tourism, Triund trekking, Dalai Lama temple, McLeod Ganj shopping, Tibetan food in McLeod Ganj.', 'McLeod Ganj is a small town located in the northern Indian state of Himachal Pradesh. It is known for its natural beauty and spiritual significance', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">McLeod Ganj is a small town located in the northern Indian state of Himachal Pradesh. It is known for its natural beauty and spiritual significance. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in McLeod Ganj:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Namgyal Monastery: The Namgyal Monastery is a Tibetan Buddhist monastery located in McLeod Ganj. It was established in the 16th century by the third Dalai Lama and is now the largest Tibetan monastery outside of Tibet. The monastery houses a number of valuable Buddhist artifacts, including ancient Tibetan texts, statues, and paintings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tsuglagkhang Complex: The Tsuglagkhang Complex is the official residence of the Dalai Lama in India. It is also a major pilgrimage site for Buddhists from all over the world. The complex houses a number of important Tibetan Buddhist temples, including the Tsuglagkhang Temple, the Kalachakra Temple, and the Namgyal Gompa.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Bhagsu Waterfall: The Bhagsu Waterfall is a popular tourist attraction in McLeod Ganj. It is located about 2 kilometers from the town center and is known for its natural beauty and serenity. The waterfall is surrounded by lush green forests and is a great place to relax and unwind.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dharamkot: Dharamkot is a small village located about 2 kilometers from McLeod Ganj. It is known for its scenic beauty and tranquil atmosphere. The village is surrounded by dense forests and offers stunning views of the Himalayas.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Triund: Triund is a popular trekking destination located about 9 kilometers from McLeod Ganj. The trek to Triund is relatively easy and takes about 4-5 hours to complete. The trek offers stunning views of the Dhauladhar range and is a great way to experience the natural beauty of the region.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tibetan Museum: The Tibetan Museum is located in the Tsuglagkhang Complex and is dedicated to preserving the history and culture of the Tibetan people. The museum houses a number of valuable artifacts, including ancient Tibetan texts, paintings, and sculptures.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Overall, McLeod Ganj is a great place to visit for those interested in Buddhism and nature. Its serene atmosphere and stunning natural beauty make it a popular destination for tourists from all over the world.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=32.24257579999999%2C76.32127809999999&z=14', '2023-05-12 11:01:32', '2023-05-12 11:01:32'),
(106, 'India', 'Uttarakhand', 'Mussoorie', 'mussoorie', 'Mussoorie Tourist Places', 'Mussoorie tourism, Mussoorie sightseeing, Places to visit in Mussoorie, Mussoorie hill stations, Western Himalayan tourism, Kempty Falls tourism, Mussoorie trekking, Adventure tourism in Mussoorie, Mussoorie shopping, Mussoorie resorts.', 'Mussoorie, also known as the \"Queen of Hills,\" is a picturesque hill station located in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. It is a popular tourist destination due to its beautiful landscapes, pleasant climate, and serene atmosphere.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mussoorie, also known as the \"Queen of Hills,\" is a picturesque hill station located in the Indian state of Uttarakhand. It is a popular tourist destination due to its beautiful landscapes, pleasant climate, and serene atmosphere. Here are some of the must-visit tourist attractions in Mussoorie:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kempty Falls: Located about 15 km from Mussoorie, Kempty Falls is a popular spot for picnicking and bathing. It was developed by a British officer, John Mekinan, in the 19th century.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gun Hill: Situated at a height of 2,024 meters, Gun Hill is the second-highest peak in Mussoorie. It offers panoramic views of the town and the surrounding hills. The hill was used by the British to fire a gun every afternoon to help people adjust their watches.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Lal Tibba: The highest peak in Mussoorie, Lal Tibba offers breathtaking views of the Himalayan range. It is located about 5 km from Mussoorie and was named after a British officer, Mr. Young.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mussoorie Lake: A man-made lake located about 6 km from Mussoorie, Mussoorie Lake is a perfect spot for boating and picnicking. It was developed by the City Board and the Mussoorie Dehradun Development Authority in 2006.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Christ Church: Built in 1836, Christ Church is the oldest church in the Himalayan region. It is located near the Library Chowk and is known for its stained-glass windows.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mussoorie is a perfect getaway for those seeking respite from the hustle and bustle of city life. Its serene atmosphere, beautiful landscapes, and pleasant weather make it an ideal destination for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. So, pack your bags and head to Mussoorie for a memorable vacation amidst the hills.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=30.459789199999992%2C78.0643723&z=14', '2023-05-12 11:03:45', '2023-05-12 11:03:45'),
(107, 'India', 'Maharashtra', 'pune', 'pune', 'Pune touristy places', 'Pune tourism, Pune sightseeing, Places to visit in Pune, Pune culture, Historical places in Pune, Western Ghats tourism, Adventure tourism in Pune, Pune food, Pune shopping, Pune resorts.', 'Pune is a city of historic significance, cultural diversity, and natural beauty. It offers a plethora of experiences that attract tourists from across the globe.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pune touristy places</strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pune is a city of historic significance, cultural diversity, and natural beauty. It offers a plethora of experiences that attract tourists from across the globe. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Pune:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shaniwar Wada - Built in the 18th century, this magnificent fortification was once the seat of the Peshwas of the Maratha Empire.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Aga Khan Palace - This palace served as a refuge for Mahatma Gandhi and his wife during the Quit India Movement in 1942.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sinhagad Fort - This fort stands tall at an altitude of 1,300 meters above sea level and was once the site of many battles in the Maratha empire.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Osho Ashram - This spiritual center attracts people from all over the world seeking peace and tranquility.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dagdusheth Halwai Ganpati Temple - This temple is devoted to Lord Ganesha and is visited by thousands of devotees every day.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pataleshwar Cave Temple - This temple is an architectural wonder that dates back to the 8th century.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum - This museum houses a vast collection of Indian artifacts, including ancient swords, musical instruments, and textiles.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Rajiv Gandhi Zoological Park - This zoo is home to a diverse range of wildlife, including tigers, leopards, and snakes.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pune is a city that has something to offer to everyone. Whether you\'re a history buff, a nature lover, or a spiritual seeker, Pune has plenty of experiences that will leave you enchanted. So, come and explore this beautiful city and create memories that will last a lifetime!</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=18.524652567130726%2C73.86296740000002&z=11', '2023-05-12 11:17:33', '2023-05-12 11:18:37'),
(109, 'India', 'Uttarakhand', 'rishikesh', 'rishikesh', 'RISHIKESH TOURISTY PLACES', 'Rishikesh tourism, Rishikesh sightseeing, Places to visit in Rishikesh, Adventure tourism in Rishikesh, Rishikesh rafting, Rishikesh yoga, Rishikesh ashrams, Ganga Aarti, Rishikesh trekking, Rishikesh camping.', 'Nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas, Rishikesh is a city that holds great spiritual significance for Hindus. The city is situated on the banks of the holy river Ganga and is home to several ancient temples, ashrams, and ghats.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Nestled in the foothills of the Himalayas, Rishikesh is a city that holds great spiritual significance for Hindus. The city is situated on the banks of the holy river Ganga and is home to several ancient temples, ashrams, and ghats.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most significant places in Rishikesh is the Triveni Ghat, where the three holy rivers of Ganga, Yamuna, and Saraswati converge. It is believed that taking a dip in the Triveni Ghat will wash away all sins and provide moksha or liberation from the cycle of birth and death.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Parmarth Niketan is another important ashram in Rishikesh, which was established by Swami Shukdevanandji Maharaj in 1942. The ashram is known for its yoga and meditation programs, and visitors can attend various workshops and classes.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Neelkanth Mahadev Temple is also a must-visit place in Rishikesh. The temple is situated at a height of 1,330 meters and is dedicated to Lord Shiva. It is believed that Lord Shiva consumed poison at this spot, which turned his throat blue, hence the name Neelkanth.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Beatles Ashram, also known as the Maharishi Mahesh Yogi Ashram, is a popular tourist spot in Rishikesh. The ashram was made famous by the Beatles, who visited it in 1968 to learn transcendental meditation from Maharishi Mahesh Yogi.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Rishikesh is also known as the \'Yoga Capital of the World\' and attracts thousands of visitors from around the globe every year to attend various yoga and meditation retreats.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Rishikesh is a city that offers a unique blend of spirituality, adventure, and tranquility. Its temples, ashrams, and ghats hold great significance in Hindu mythology and offer visitors an opportunity to experience the rich cultural heritage of India. Whether you are seeking spiritual solace or adventure sports, Rishikesh has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=30.087690132289637%2C78.27060874999998&z=12', '2023-05-12 11:30:34', '2023-05-12 11:30:34'),
(110, 'India', 'Meghalaya', 'shillong', 'shillong', 'Shillong Touristy Places', 'Shillong tourism, Shillong sightseeing, Places to visit in Shillong, Shillong hill stations, Northeast India tourism, Shillong waterfalls, Shillong trekking, Adventure tourism in Shillong, Shillong music festivals, Shillong shopping.', 'Shillong, the capital city of Meghalaya, is a charming hill station that attracts tourists from all over the world. It is known for its pleasant climate, stunning landscapes, and the rich cultural heritage of its people.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shillong, the capital city of Meghalaya, is a charming hill station that attracts tourists from all over the world. It is known for its pleasant climate, stunning landscapes, and the rich cultural heritage of its people. Here are some of the must-visit tourist places in Shillong:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shillong Peak: The highest point in the city, Shillong Peak offers a panoramic view of the surrounding hills and valleys. It is a popular spot for trekking and hiking.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Ward\'s Lake: This picturesque lake, located in the heart of the city, is a popular spot for picnics and boating. It is surrounded by lush greenery and has a variety of flora and fauna.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Don Bosco Centre for Indigenous Cultures: This museum showcases the rich cultural heritage of the indigenous people of the Northeast. It has several galleries that exhibit artifacts, paintings, and photographs that highlight the region\'s art, culture, and history.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Elephant Falls: This beautiful waterfall, located just outside the city, is named after an elephant-shaped rock near the waterfall. It is surrounded by lush green forests and is a popular spot for picnics and trekking.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Laitlum Canyons: This stunning canyon, located on the outskirts of the city, offers a breathtaking view of the surrounding hills and valleys. It is a popular spot for trekking and photography.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shillong is a must-visit destination for nature lovers, adventure enthusiasts, and those who want to explore the rich cultural heritage of Northeast India. With its stunning landscapes, pleasant weather, and rich cultural diversity, Shillong promises to be an unforgettable experience for anyone who visits.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=25.590146823212567%2C91.89243715&z=12', '2023-05-12 11:32:11', '2023-05-12 11:32:11');
