(111, 'India', 'Jammu and Kashmir', 'srinagar', 'srinagar', 'Srinagar Touristy Places', 'Srinagar tourism, Srinagar sightseeing, Places to visit in Srinagar, Srinagar houseboats, Kashmir tourism, Mughal gardens in Srinagar, Dal Lake tourism, Adventure tourism in Srinagar, Srinagar handicrafts, Srinagar shopping.', 'Srinagar is a popular tourist destination in the northernmost state of India, Jammu and Kashmir. It is also known as the \"Venice of the East\" because of its beautiful Dal Lake, Mughal Gardens, and traditional houseboats. The Mughal Gardens, including Shalimar Bagh, Nishat Bagh, and Chashma Shahi, were built during the Mughal era and are a must-visit for their stunning beauty and historical significance. Other popular tourist attractions in Srinagar include the Hazratbal Shrine, Shankaracharya Temple, and Pari Mahal. Srinagar is known as the \"Paradise on Earth\" for a reason. This beautiful city is located in the Kashmir Valley and is surrounded by snow-capped mountains, glistening lakes, and serene gardens.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Srinagar is a popular tourist destination in the northernmost state of India, Jammu and Kashmir. It is also known as the \"Venice of the East\" because of its beautiful Dal Lake, Mughal Gardens, and traditional houseboats. The Mughal Gardens, including Shalimar Bagh, Nishat Bagh, and Chashma Shahi, were built during the Mughal era and are a must-visit for their stunning beauty and historical significance. Other popular tourist attractions in Srinagar include the Hazratbal Shrine, Shankaracharya Temple, and Pari Mahal. Srinagar is known as the \"Paradise on Earth\" for a reason. This beautiful city is located in the Kashmir Valley and is surrounded by snow-capped mountains, glistening lakes, and serene gardens. Here are some of the most popular tourist attractions in Srinagar:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Dal Lake: This famous lake is the centerpiece of Srinagar and is known for its breathtaking beauty. Visitors can take a shikara ride on the lake, which is surrounded by majestic mountains, floating gardens, and vibrant houseboats.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mughal Gardens: Srinagar is home to several beautiful Mughal gardens, including Shalimar Bagh, Nishat Bagh, and Chashme Shahi. These gardens were built by the Mughal emperors in the 16th and 17th centuries and are known for their stunning architecture and manicured lawns.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Hazratbal Shrine: This holy shrine is located on the banks of Dal Lake and is considered to be one of the most important Muslim shrines in India. It houses a relic believed to be a hair from the Prophet Muhammad\'s beard.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Shankaracharya Temple: This ancient temple is perched on top of a hill and is dedicated to Lord Shiva. It was built in the 9th century and is believed to be one of the oldest temples in the region.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Pari Mahal: This historic monument is located on a hilltop and was once a Buddhist monastery. It was later converted into a school of astrology by the Mughal emperor Shah Jahan.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Srinagar is truly a paradise on earth and its natural beauty and rich cultural heritage will leave you mesmerized. Whether you are looking for adventure, relaxation, or spiritual enlightenment, this city has something for everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=25.590146823212567%2C91.89243715&z=12', '2023-05-12 11:34:30', '2023-05-12 11:34:30'),
(112, 'India', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Vishakhapatnam', 'vishakhapatnam', 'Visakhapatnam Tourist Places', 'Visakhapatnam tourism, Visakhapatnam sightseeing, Places to visit in Visakhapatnam, Beaches in Visakhapatnam, Eastern Ghats tourism, Araku Valley tourism, Borra Caves tourism, Adventure tourism in Visakhapatnam, Visakhapatnam food, Visakhapatnam shopping.', 'Visakhapatnam, also known as Vizag, is a coastal city in the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. It is a popular tourist destination known for its scenic beaches, natural beauty, and rich cultural heritage.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><strong style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Visakhapatnam Tourist Places</strong></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Visakhapatnam, also known as Vizag, is a coastal city in the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. It is a popular tourist destination known for its scenic beaches, natural beauty, and rich cultural heritage. Here are some of the touristy places to visit in Visakhapatnam:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kailasagiri: Kailasagiri is a hilltop park that offers stunning panoramic views of the city and the Bay of Bengal. It is a popular spot for picnics, leisure walks, and outdoor activities. The park features several attractions, including a giant statue of Lord Shiva and Parvati, a toy train, a ropeway, and an amphitheater.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Yarada Beach: Yarada Beach is a pristine and secluded beach located about 15 km from the city center. It is a popular spot for swimming, sunbathing, and relaxing amidst nature. The beach offers breathtaking views of the sea and the surrounding hills.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Borra Caves: Borra Caves is a natural wonder located about 90 km from Visakhapatnam. It is a network of limestone caves that feature stunning stalactite and stalagmite formations. The caves are believed to be millions of years old and are home to several unique species of bats and insects.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Rushikonda Beach: Rushikonda Beach is a popular tourist spot located about 10 km from Visakhapatnam. It is a picturesque beach with soft golden sand, clear blue water, and lush greenery. The beach offers several water sports activities, including jet skiing, parasailing, and windsurfing.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Araku Valley: Araku Valley is a scenic hill station located about 120 km from Visakhapatnam. It is known for its natural beauty, coffee plantations, and tribal culture. The valley is home to several waterfalls, caves, and viewpoints that offer breathtaking views of the surrounding hills and forests.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Visakhapatnam is a must-visit destination for anyone looking to explore the natural beauty and rich cultural heritage of Andhra Pradesh.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=17.686815900000013%2C83.2184815&z=12', '2023-05-12 11:38:26', '2023-05-12 11:38:26'),
(113, 'India', 'Maharashtra', 'mumbai', 'mumbai', 'MUMBAI TOURIST PLACES', 'Mumbai tourism, Mumbai sightseeing, Places to visit in Mumbai, Mumbai culture, Historical places in Mumbai, Mumbai beaches, Adventure tourism in Mumbai, Mumbai food, Mumbai shopping, Mumbai nightlife.', 'Mumbai, formerly known as Bombay, is a bustling city located on the west coast of India. It is India\'s financial, commercial, and entertainment capital, attracting thousands of visitors every year. Mumbai is known for its rich history, culture, and architecture.', 'mumbai-thumbnail-168389239056466.jpeg', 'Mumbai_thumbnail', NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mumbai, formerly known as Bombay, is a bustling city located on the west coast of India. It is India\'s financial, commercial, and entertainment capital, attracting thousands of visitors every year. Mumbai is known for its rich history, culture, and architecture. Here are some of the must-visit tourist places in Mumbai:</span></p><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Gateway of India - The Gateway of India is an iconic monument located in South Mumbai. It was built in 1924 to commemorate the visit of King George V and Queen Mary to Mumbai. The monument is a great place to take a walk and enjoy the stunning views of the Arabian Sea.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Marine Drive - Marine Drive is a 3.6-kilometer-long boulevard located in South Mumbai. It is also known as the \"Queen\'s Necklace\" because of the way the streetlights resemble a necklace at night. The promenade is a great place to take a leisurely walk and enjoy the beautiful views of the Arabian Sea.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus - Chhatrapati Shivaji Terminus, also known as Victoria Terminus, is a historic railway station located in South Mumbai. It was built in 1887 and is a UNESCO World Heritage Site. The station is known for its beautiful Gothic architecture and is one of the busiest railway stations in India.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Elephanta Caves - The Elephanta Caves are a network of rock-cut caves located on the Elephanta Island, just a short ferry ride away from Mumbai. The caves are believed to have been built between the 5th and 8th centuries and are a UNESCO World Heritage Site. They are known for their beautiful sculptures and carvings, many of which are dedicated to Lord Shiva.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: transparent;\">Juhu Beach - Juhu Beach is one of the most popular beaches in Mumbai. It is a great place to relax and enjoy the views of the Arabian Sea. The beach is also known for its street food and is a must-visit for anyone interested in trying out some authentic Mumbai cuisine.</span></li></ul><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mumbai is a city with a unique and vibrant culture, and each of these places has its own unique history and significance. Visiting these places will give you a deeper understanding of the city\'s rich cultural heritage and its importance as Indias financial and commercial center.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=19.0823590243553%2C72.88118614999998&z=10', '2023-05-12 11:53:12', '2023-05-12 11:53:13'),
(114, 'India', 'Kerala', 'Wayanad', 'wayanad', 'Wayanad Tourist Places', 'Wayanad tourism, Wayanad sightseeing, Places to visit in Wayanad, Western Ghats tourism, Wayanad hill stations, Wayanad wildlife sanctuary, Wayanad trekking, Adventure tourism in Wayanad, Wayanad tea plantations, Wayanad waterfalls.', 'Wayanad, located in the northern part of Kerala, is a land of pristine beauty, lush greenery, and mesmerizing waterfalls. This scenic destination is blessed with a rich cultural heritage, which is evident in the many tourist attractions it boasts of.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Wayanad, located in the northern part of Kerala, is a land of pristine beauty, lush greenery, and mesmerizing waterfalls. This scenic destination is blessed with a rich cultural heritage, which is evident in the many tourist attractions it boasts of.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the must-visit places in Wayanad is the Edakkal Caves, which are situated on Ambukuthi Hills. These caves feature ancient rock art that is believed to date back to the Neolithic Age, making them a valuable archeological site. Visitors can witness the breathtaking views of the surrounding hills and valleys from the top of the Ambukuthi Hills.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another significant landmark in Wayanad is the Banasura Sagar Dam, which is the largest earthen dam in India. The dam is built across the Karamanathodu tributary of River Kabini and is surrounded by picturesque mountains. The dam is a major tourist attraction and offers activities like boating, trekking, and island camping to its visitors.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Pookode Lake, situated at the heart of Wayanad, is another popular destination among tourists. The freshwater lake is surrounded by lush greenery and offers boating facilities. The lake also has a freshwater aquarium and a children\'s park, making it an ideal family destination.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Wayanad Wildlife Sanctuary, which is home to a wide variety of flora and fauna, is a must-visit destination for nature lovers. The sanctuary is home to animals like tigers, elephants, leopards, and many species of birds. Visitors can take a jeep safari or an elephant ride to explore the sanctuary.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Wayanad is a treasure trove of scenic beauty, archeological sites, and wildlife sanctuaries that offer something for every kind of traveler. With its unique blend of culture, history, and nature, Wayanad is truly a paradise waiting to be explored.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=28.92912090000002%2C77.09477869999998&z=10', '2023-05-12 12:48:08', '2023-05-12 12:48:08'),
(115, 'India', 'Andhra Pradesh', 'Tirupati', 'tirupati', 'Tirupati Tourist Places', 'Tirupati tourism, Tirupati sightseeing, Places to visit in Tirupati, Tirumala temple tourism, Andhra Pradesh tourism, Tirupati laddu, Tirupati darshan, Tirupati shopping, Adventure tourism in Tirupati, Tirupati Balaji.', 'Tirupati is a must-visit destination for all those seeking a spiritual getaway. The city is renowned for its stunning temples and ancient architectural marvels that leave visitors mesmerized. One of the most famous landmarks in Tirupati is the Sri Venkateswara Temple, which is dedicated to Lord Vishnu and attracts millions of devotees every year. The temple is said to have been built in the 10th century and is adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures that showcase the grandeur of the Dravidian architecture.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Tirupati is a must-visit destination for all those seeking a spiritual getaway. The city is renowned for its stunning temples and ancient architectural marvels that leave visitors mesmerized. One of the most famous landmarks in Tirupati is the Sri Venkateswara Temple, which is dedicated to Lord Vishnu and attracts millions of devotees every year. The temple is said to have been built in the 10th century and is adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures that showcase the grandeur of the Dravidian architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another popular destination in Tirupati is the Sri Govindarajaswami Temple, which is situated in the heart of the city. The temple is known for its stunning architecture and beautiful surroundings. It is believed to have been built in the 12th century and is dedicated to Lord Vishnu. The temple is a must-visit destination for all those seeking inner peace and spiritual enlightenment.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Apart from these famous temples, Tirupati also has several other tourist spots that are worth exploring. One of the most popular ones is the Sri Venkateswara National Park, which is spread over an area of 353 sq km and is home to several species of wildlife. The park is an ideal destination for nature lovers and wildlife enthusiasts and offers a unique experience to visitors.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Chandragiri Fort is another famous tourist spot in Tirupati that is worth visiting. The fort was built in the 11th century and served as the capital of the Vijayanagara Empire. It is situated atop a hill and offers breathtaking views of the surrounding landscape.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Tirupati is a city that is steeped in history and culture. Its stunning temples, ancient forts, and natural beauty make it an ideal destination for all those seeking a spiritual and cultural getaway. Whether you are a history buff, nature lover, or simply seeking inner peace, Tirupati has something to offer to everyone.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=13.62766095923191%2C79.42480085000001&z=12', '2023-05-12 12:50:26', '2023-05-12 12:50:26'),
(116, 'India', 'Kerala', 'Thiruvananthapuram', 'thiruvananthapuram', 'Thiruvananthapuram Tourist Places', 'Thiruvananthapuram tourism, Thiruvananthapuram sightseeing, Places to visit in Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala tourism, Thiruvananthapuram beaches, Padmanabhaswamy temple tourism, Kovalam tourism, Adventure tourism in Thiruvananthapuram, Thiruvananthapuram foo', 'Thiruvananthapuram, also known as Trivandrum, is the capital city of the beautiful state of Kerala. This city has a rich cultural and historical heritage, with a variety of tourist attractions that attract travelers from all over the world. One of the most famous landmarks of Thiruvananthapuram is the Sri Padmanabhaswamy Temple, an ancient Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu. The temple was built in the Dravidian style of architecture and has a grand entrance, adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures. The temple is a significant religious site for Hindus and holds immense historical importance.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thiruvananthapuram, also known as Trivandrum, is the capital city of the beautiful state of Kerala. This city has a rich cultural and historical heritage, with a variety of tourist attractions that attract travelers from all over the world. One of the most famous landmarks of Thiruvananthapuram is the Sri Padmanabhaswamy Temple, an ancient Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Vishnu. The temple was built in the Dravidian style of architecture and has a grand entrance, adorned with intricate carvings and sculptures. The temple is a significant religious site for Hindus and holds immense historical importance.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another must-visit place in Thiruvananthapuram is the Napier Museum. It is a stunning 19th-century building constructed in the Indo-Saracenic style and houses a vast collection of art and artifacts. The museum has a beautiful garden surrounding it, making it a perfect spot for a picnic or leisurely stroll.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Kovalam beach is a popular destination for tourists in Thiruvananthapuram, with its golden sand and clear blue waters. The beach is surrounded by coconut trees and offers a picturesque view of the sea. Visitors can also enjoy various water sports activities such as swimming, surfing, and parasailing.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Kanakakunnu Palace, built by the Travancore royal family, is a magnificent palace situated in the heart of the city. The palace is now converted into a cultural center and hosts various cultural events throughout the year, including music concerts and dance performances.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thiruvananthapuram is also famous for its delicious cuisine, which is a blend of various South Indian and Kerala dishes. The local street food scene is a must-try for food lovers, offering delicious snacks and dishes like idli, dosa, vada, and banana chips.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Thiruvananthapuram is a perfect destination for travelers looking for a cultural and historical experience. The city offers a unique blend of ancient architecture, scenic beaches, and delicious cuisine, making it a great place to visit for anyone seeking a memorable vacation.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=8.524139099999982%2C76.93663760000003&z=12', '2023-05-12 12:52:46', '2023-05-12 12:52:46'),
(117, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Thanjavur', 'thanjavur', 'Thanjavur Tourist Places', 'Thanjavur tourism, Thanjavur sightseeing, Places to visit in Thanjavur, Tamil Nadu tourism, Brihadeeswara temple tourism, Thanjavur paintings, Thanjavur cuisine, Adventure tourism in Thanjavur, Thanjavur art and craft, Thanjavur Royal Palace.', 'Thanjavur, also known as Tanjore, is a beautiful city in the Indian state of Tamil Nadu that is steeped in history and culture. The city is famous for its magnificent temples, stunning architecture, and exquisite art.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thanjavur, also known as Tanjore, is a beautiful city in the Indian state of Tamil Nadu that is steeped in history and culture. The city is famous for its magnificent temples, stunning architecture, and exquisite art. Some of the popular tourist attractions in Thanjavur are:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Brihadeeswarar Temple: Built during the Chola dynasty in the 11th century, Brihadeeswarar Temple is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the largest temples in India. The temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and boasts of stunning architecture and intricate carvings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thanjavur Palace: Thanjavur Palace was the official residence of the Thanjavur Maratha rulers. The palace is a fine example of the Maratha style of architecture and houses a museum that showcases the history and culture of the region.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Saraswathi Mahal Library: The Saraswathi Mahal Library is one of the oldest libraries in Asia, established in the 16th century. It houses a vast collection of ancient palm-leaf manuscripts, rare books, and paintings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sangeetha Mahal: Sangeetha Mahal is a historic building that was used for conducting music concerts during the reign of the Nayakas. The building is renowned for its unique acoustics, which make it an ideal venue for musical performances.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Schwartz Church: Schwartz Church, also known as the New Jerusalem Church, is a beautiful church built in the 18th century by the Danish missionary, Bartholomaeus Ziegenbalg. The church is known for its stunning architecture and peaceful surroundings.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thanjavur is a city that offers a glimpse into the rich cultural heritage of Tamil Nadu. From the magnificent temples to the historic palaces and libraries, the city is a treasure trove of ancient architecture and art. A visit to Thanjavur is a must for anyone interested in history, culture, and architecture.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=10.752829819708198%2C79.13144940000002&z=12', '2023-05-12 12:54:25', '2023-05-12 12:54:25'),
(118, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'rameshwaram', 'rameshwaram', 'Rameshwaram Tourist Places', 'Rameshwaram tourism, Rameshwaram sightseeing, Places to visit in Rameshwaram, Tamil Nadu tourism, Ramanathaswamy temple tourism, Rameshwaram beaches, Rameshwaram cuisine, Adventure tourism in Rameshwaram, Rameshwaram bridge, Rameshwaram water sports.', 'Rameshwaram, also known as the \"Varanasi of the South,\" is a holy city located on the Pamban Island in Tamil Nadu. It is a significant pilgrimage site for Hindus, and thousands of devotees visit every year to take a dip in the holy waters and offer their prayers at the temples.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Rameshwaram, also known as the \"Varanasi of the South,\" is a holy city located on the Pamban Island in Tamil Nadu. It is a significant pilgrimage site for Hindus, and thousands of devotees visit every year to take a dip in the holy waters and offer their prayers at the temples.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Ramanathaswamy Temple is the most famous and significant attraction in Rameshwaram. Built-in the 17th century, this magnificent temple is dedicated to Lord Shiva and features stunning Dravidian architecture. The temple is one of the twelve Jyotirlingas in India and is believed to be the place where Lord Rama built a bridge across the sea to reach Lanka to rescue his wife Sita from Ravana.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another must-visit place in Rameshwaram is the Agnitheertham, which is located just outside the Ramanathaswamy Temple. This holy water body is believed to have medicinal properties and is considered sacred by Hindus. Devotees take a dip in the water before visiting the temple.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Gandhamadhana Parvatham is another popular spot in Rameshwaram. It is a small hillock that offers a panoramic view of the entire island. According to Hindu mythology, Lord Hanuman placed his foot on the hill while on his way to Lanka to rescue Sita.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Pamban Bridge is a significant engineering marvel in Rameshwaram. Built-in 1914, it is the longest railway bridge in India and connects Rameshwaram to mainland India. The bridge offers breathtaking views of the sea and is a popular spot for photography.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Rameshwaram is a city steeped in rich Hindu mythology and is a must-visit destination for anyone interested in spirituality and history. The temples and other attractions in the city offer a glimpse into India\'s ancient past and are sure to leave a lasting impression on visitors.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=9.286718739371608%2C79.31163309999998&z=14', '2023-05-12 12:56:43', '2023-05-12 12:56:43'),
(119, 'India', 'Karnataka', 'Mangalore', 'mangalore', 'Mangalore Tourist Places', 'Mangalore tourism, Mangalore sightseeing, Places to visit in Mangalore, Beaches in Mangalore, Karnataka tourism, Mangalore cuisine, Adventure tourism in Mangalore, Mangalore temples, Mangalore shopping, Mangalore ports.', 'angalore, also known as Mangaluru, is a picturesque coastal city located in the southwestern state of Karnataka in India. It is a city that boasts a rich history, culture, and stunning natural beauty', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mangalore, also known as Mangaluru, is a picturesque coastal city located in the southwestern state of Karnataka in India. It is a city that boasts a rich history, culture, and stunning natural beauty. Here are some of the top tourist attractions in Mangalore that you can\'t miss:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kadri Manjunath Temple: This temple is one of the oldest in Mangalore and is dedicated to Lord Shiva. It is believed to have been built during the 10th century and is a perfect example of the unique style of architecture that was prevalent during that time.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">St. Aloysius Chapel: This beautiful chapel is situated in the heart of the city and is known for its stunning murals and frescoes that depict the life of Jesus Christ. The chapel was built by the Jesuit missionaries in the 19th century and is a must-visit for art lovers.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Panambur Beach: This is one of the most popular beaches in Mangalore and is known for its pristine white sands and crystal-clear waters. It is a perfect place to relax and unwind and offers a range of water sports activities for adventure enthusiasts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mangaladevi Temple: This temple is dedicated to Goddess Mangaladevi and is one of the most famous temples in Mangalore. It is believed to have been built during the 9th century and is an excellent example of the unique style of temple architecture that was prevalent during that period.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Sultan Battery: This is an ancient watchtower that was built by the legendary ruler Tipu Sultan. It offers a breathtaking view of the surrounding landscape and is a must-visit for history buffs.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Mangalore is a city that has something for everyone. Whether you are a history buff, an art lover, a nature enthusiast, or just looking for a place to relax, Mangalore has it all. Don\'t miss out on the opportunity to explore this beautiful city and its hidden gems.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=12.914141699999984%2C74.85595680000002&z=14', '2023-05-12 12:59:20', '2023-05-12 12:59:20'),
(120, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'mahabalipuram', 'mahabalipuram', 'Mahabalipuram Tourist Places', 'Mahabalipuram tourism, Mahabalipuram sightseeing, Places to visit in Mahabalipuram, Tamil Nadu tourism, Mahabalipuram monuments, Mahabalipuram beaches, Shore temple tourism, Adventure tourism in Mahabalipuram, Mahabalipuram stone carvings, Mahabalipuram a', 'Mahabalipuram, also known as Mamallapuram, is a coastal town located in the southern state of Tamil Nadu in India. It is famous for its historic temples and monuments that are a testament to the rich cultural heritage of India.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Mahabalipuram, also known as Mamallapuram, is a coastal town located in the southern state of Tamil Nadu in India. It is famous for its historic temples and monuments that are a testament to the rich cultural heritage of India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most popular tourist attractions in Mahabalipuram is the Shore Temple, which was built in the 8th century by the Pallava dynasty. It is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and is renowned for its intricate carvings and intricate architecture. The temple was built to honor Lord Shiva and is believed to be one of the oldest structural stone temples in South India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another must-visit destination in Mahabalipuram is the Pancha Rathas, or the Five Chariots. These are monolithic structures carved out of granite that are shaped like chariots and are dedicated to the five Pandava brothers from the Indian epic, Mahabharata. The Pancha Rathas are a classic example of Indian rock-cut architecture and are believed to have been built in the 7th century.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Mahabalipuram beach is also a popular spot for tourists, offering stunning views of the Bay of Bengal and a variety of water sports. The beach is lined with food stalls selling fresh seafood, making it a popular destination for foodies.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">The Five Rathas, Krishna\'s Butterball, and Mahabalipuram lighthouse are other attractions that should not be missed when visiting this historic town.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Mahabalipuram is a treasure trove of history and culture, offering visitors a glimpse into the rich heritage of India. With its beautiful temples, ancient monuments, and stunning beaches, it is a must-visit destination for any traveler seeking to explore the country\'s rich past and vibrant present.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=12.622328194693837%2C80.19114229999998&z=13', '2023-05-12 13:00:57', '2023-05-12 13:00:57'),
(121, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Kanchipuram', 'kanchipuram', 'Kanchipuram Tourist Places', 'Kanchipuram tourism, Kanchipuram sightseeing, Places to visit in Kanchipuram, Tamil Nadu tourism, Kanchipuram silk sarees, Kanchipuram temples, Kanchipuram culture, Adventure tourism in Kanchipuram, Kanchipuram food, Kanchipuram shopping.', 'Kanchipuram, also known as the \"City of Thousand Temples,\" is a beautiful destination with a rich cultural heritage and history. The city has been a significant religious center since the ancient times of the Pallava dynasty. Kanchipuram is home to various temples, including Kailasanathar Temple, Kamakshi Amman Temple, and Varadharaja Perumal Temple.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kanchipuram, also known as the \"City of Thousand Temples,\" is a beautiful destination with a rich cultural heritage and history. The city has been a significant religious center since the ancient times of the Pallava dynasty. Kanchipuram is home to various temples, including Kailasanathar Temple, Kamakshi Amman Temple, and Varadharaja Perumal Temple.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kailasanathar Temple, built in the early 8th century, is one of the oldest and most important temples in Kanchipuram. It is dedicated to Lord Shiva and is known for its beautiful carvings and architecture. The temple was built by the Pallava dynasty, and it is believed that it was constructed by Rajasimha. It is a perfect example of Dravidian architecture and is known for its intricate carvings and stunning sculptures.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kamakshi Amman Temple, built in the 14th century, is another significant temple in Kanchipuram. It is dedicated to Goddess Kamakshi, who is believed to be an incarnation of Goddess Parvati. The temple is known for its beautiful architecture and intricate carvings. It was built by the Cholas, and later, it was renovated by the Vijayanagara kings. The temple has a golden chariot, which is taken out during festive occasions.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Varadharaja Perumal Temple, built in the 11th century, is another important temple in Kanchipuram. It is dedicated to Lord Vishnu and is known for its magnificent architecture. The temple was built by the Cholas and was later renovated by the Vijayanagara kings. The temple has a beautiful gopuram and is known for its stunning sculptures.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kanchipuram is not just about temples. The city is also famous for its silk sarees, which are made from the finest silk and are famous all over the world. The sarees are handwoven and are known for their intricate designs and vibrant colors. The city is also famous for its delicious cuisine, including idlis, dosas, and vadas.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Kanchipuram is a must-visit destination for anyone who wants to experience the rich cultural heritage and history of South India. The temples in Kanchipuram are known for their beautiful architecture and intricate carvings, while the city\'s silk sarees are famous all over the world. The cuisine of Kanchipuram is also a must-try, with its delicious flavors and unique preparations. A visit to Kanchipuram is an excellent way to experience the beauty and diversity of South India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=13.722520400000043%2C76.4722143&z=13', '2023-05-12 13:02:32', '2023-05-12 13:02:32'),
(122, 'India', 'Tamil Nadu', 'Kanyakumari', 'kanyakumari', 'Kanayakumari Tourist Places', 'Kanyakumari tourism, Kanyakumari sightseeing, Places to visit in Kanyakumari, Tamil Nadu tourism, Kanyakumari sunrise, Kanyakumari sunset, Vivekananda Rock Memorial tourism, Adventure tourism in Kanyakumari, Kanyakumari beaches, Kanyakumari culture.', 'Kanyakumari, located at the southernmost tip of India, is a place of immense natural beauty and cultural significance. The town is home to a plethora of tourist attractions that have lured visitors from all over the world.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kanyakumari, located at the southernmost tip of India, is a place of immense natural beauty and cultural significance. The town is home to a plethora of tourist attractions that have lured visitors from all over the world. Here are some of the must-visit places in Kanyakumari:</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Vivekananda Rock Memorial: The memorial was built in the memory of Swami Vivekananda, a famous Indian philosopher and spiritual leader who meditated on this rock in 1892. The rock also houses a meditation hall, where visitors can meditate and seek solace.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Thiruvalluvar Statue: The statue is a tribute to the great Tamil poet and philosopher, Thiruvalluvar. The statue stands tall at a height of 133 feet, with 38 feet representing the 38 chapters of Thirukkural, a Tamil classic.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kanyakumari Temple: The temple is dedicated to Goddess Kanyakumari, also known as Devi Kumari. The temple is said to have been built by Parasurama, an incarnation of Lord Vishnu, and is one of the 51 Shakti Peethas in India.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gandhi Memorial: The memorial is built in the memory of Mahatma Gandhi, the father of the nation. It is located at the place where his ashes were kept before immersion in the sea.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Padmanabhapuram Palace: The palace is located about 20 km from Kanyakumari and was built in the 16th century by the kings of the Travancore dynasty. It is known for its intricate wood carvings and is a must-visit for history enthusiasts.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Kanyakumari is also famous for its stunning sunrises and sunsets, which can be witnessed from the southernmost tip of the country. The place holds immense significance in Indian mythology and is believed to be the place where the three seas  the Bay of Bengal, the Arabian Sea, and the Indian Ocean  merge together.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Kanyakumari is a place that offers a perfect blend of natural beauty and cultural heritage. A visit to this place is sure to leave you with a sense of peace and serenity.</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=8.088306400000016%2C77.53845070000001&z=13', '2023-05-12 13:15:17', '2023-05-12 13:15:17'),
(123, 'India', 'Karnataka', 'Gokarna', 'gokarna', 'Gokarna Tourist Places', 'Gokarna tourism, Gokarna sightseeing, Places to visit in Gokarna, Beaches in Gokarna, Karnataka tourism, Gokarna temples, Gokarna trekking, Adventure tourism in Gokarna, Gokarna water sports, Gokarna food.', 'Gokarna is a small town located in the southwestern Indian state of Karnataka. It is well known for its beautiful beaches, scenic landscapes, and ancient temples.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Gokarna is a small town located in the southwestern Indian state of Karnataka. It is well known for its beautiful beaches, scenic landscapes, and ancient temples. There are several touristy places in Gokarna that you can explore and enjoy.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most popular tourist attractions in Gokarna is the Mahabaleshwar Temple, which is dedicated to Lord Shiva. This ancient temple was built in the 4th century and is considered to be one of the holiest places for Hindus. The temple has a unique architecture and is located on the shores of the Arabian Sea, making it a picturesque location.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another must-visit place in Gokarna is the Kudle Beach, which is a perfect spot to relax and enjoy the scenic beauty of nature. The beach is surrounded by hills and offers a serene atmosphere, making it an ideal destination for those who seek peace and tranquility.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">If you are looking for some adventure, then Om Beach is the place to be. The beach is shaped like the Hindu symbol Om and offers various water sports like jet-skiing, surfing, and banana boat rides. It is also a great spot for swimming and sunbathing.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One more noteworthy place in Gokarna is the Yana Caves, which are famous for their natural rock formations and beautiful scenery. The caves are located in the Sahyadri Mountains and are believed to be over 500 million years old.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Gokarna is a perfect destination for those who seek a blend of adventure, spirituality, and relaxation. The town has something to offer for everyone, from ancient temples to beautiful beaches and adventurous water sports. A visit to this charming town is definitely worth it!</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=8.088306400000016%2C77.53845070000001&z=13', '2023-05-12 13:16:55', '2023-05-12 13:16:55'),
(124, 'India', 'Kerala', 'allepey', 'allepey', 'Allepey Tourist Places', 'Alleppey tourism, Alleppey sightseeing, Places to visit in Alleppey, Kerala tourism, Alleppey backwaters, Alleppey houseboats, Alleppey beaches, Adventure tourism in Alleppey, Alleppey cuisine, Alleppey shopping.', 'Welcome to Alleppey, a beautiful coastal town in Kerala known for its serene backwaters, pristine beaches, and lush green landscapes. Alleppey, also known as Alappuzha, is one of the most popular tourist destinations in Kerala, and rightfully so. This charming town is home to some of the most beautiful natural and man-made wonders that are sure to leave you awestruck.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Welcome to Alleppey, a beautiful coastal town in Kerala known for its serene backwaters, pristine beaches, and lush green landscapes. Alleppey, also known as Alappuzha, is one of the most popular tourist destinations in Kerala, and rightfully so. This charming town is home to some of the most beautiful natural and man-made wonders that are sure to leave you awestruck.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most iconic landmarks of Alleppey is its backwaters, which are a network of interconnected canals, lagoons, and lakes that flow into the Arabian Sea. These backwaters are a major source of livelihood for the locals and are used for transportation, fishing, and farming. You can take a leisurely boat ride along the backwaters, soak in the breathtaking views of the lush greenery, and witness the simple lifestyle of the locals.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Another major attraction of Alleppey is its beaches. The Alleppey Beach, also known as Alappuzha Beach, is a beautiful stretch of golden sand dotted with palm trees and offering a stunning view of the sunset. The beach is a popular spot for swimming, sunbathing, and surfing. The beach also has a lighthouse that offers panoramic views of the sea.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">One of the most unique and iconic experiences in Alleppey is a stay in a houseboat. These houseboats are traditional wooden boats that have been converted into floating hotels. They offer an unforgettable experience of living on water, surrounded by the lush greenery and tranquil backwaters. The houseboats come with all modern amenities, including air-conditioning, comfortable beds, and delicious local cuisine.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">Alleppey is also home to some beautiful temples, the most famous of which is the Sri Krishna Temple in Ambalappuzha. This temple is dedicated to Lord Krishna and is known for its stunning architecture and intricate carvings. The temple is also famous for its delicious sweet pudding, called \'palpayasam,\' which is offered as prasad to the devotees.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In addition to these attractions, Alleppey is also known for its coir industry, which produces some of the finest coir products in the world. You can visit a coir factory and witness the process of coir-making, from the extraction of fibers from coconut husks to the weaving of mats, rugs, and other products.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">All in all, Alleppey is a beautiful town that offers a perfect blend of natural beauty and cultural experiences. It is a must-visit destination for anyone who wants to experience the true essence of Kerala.</span></p><p><br></p><p><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">In conclusion, Alleppey is a paradise for nature lovers, adventure seekers, and cultural enthusiasts. Its backwaters, beaches, houseboats, temples, and coir industry offer a unique and unforgettable experience that you will cherish for a lifetime. So, pack your bags and head over to Alleppey to witness the magic of Kerala!</span></p><p><br></p><p><br></p>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1khK4ija128YXXPhH-rm6y3e9m8M&hl=en&ll=9.498066700000017%2C76.33884839999999&z=13', '2023-05-12 13:19:05', '2023-05-12 13:19:05');
