(7, 8, 'New Delhi', 'eduInstitute', 'Kochi', NULL, NULL, 'KOCHI WONDERLA ALLEPPEY MUNNAR THEKKADY', 'KOCHI WONDERLA ALLEPPEY MUNNAR THEKKADY', 'KOCHI COCHIN WONDERLA ALLEPPEY MUNNAR THEKKADY JAIPUR DELHI JEWISH SYNAGOGUE MATTANCHERRY PALACE Cruise vacations KOCHI HARBOR SEVEN ISLAND ERAVIKULAM NATIONAL PARK MATTUPETTY DAM WATERFALL AND ECHO POINT TEA PLANTATION PERIYAR LAKE GREEN PARK\' AYURVEDIC ', 'Munnar is a town in the Western Ghats mountain range in Indias Kerala state. A hill station and former resort for the British Raj elite, it\'s surrounded by rolling hills dotted with tea plantations established in the late 19th century. Eravikulam National Park, a habitat for the endangered mountain goat Nilgiri tahr, is home to the Lakkam Waterfalls, hiking trails and 2,695m-tall Anamudi Peak.\nKochi (also known as Cochin) is a city in southwest India\'s coastal Kerala state. It has been a port since 1341, when a flood carved out its harbor and opened it to Arab, Chinese and European merchants. Sites reflecting those influences include Fort Kochi, a settlement with tiled colonial bungalows and diverse houses of worship. Cantilevered Chinese fishing nets, typical of Kochi, have been in use for centuries.', 'kerala1jpg-1677308906864334.jpeg', 'kerala1.jpg', 'itinerary_image_63f9b3ea876fc', 'itinerary_image_63f9b3ea876f8', 7, '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Munnar</strong> is a town in the Western Ghats mountain range in Indias Kerala state. A hill station and former resort for the British Raj elite, it\'s surrounded by rolling hills dotted with tea plantations established in the late 19th century. Eravikulam National Park, a habitat for the endangered mountain goat Nilgiri tahr, is home to the Lakkam Waterfalls, hiking trails and 2,695m-tall Anamudi Peak.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Kochi </strong>(also known as Cochin) is a city in southwest India\'s coastal Kerala state. It has been a port since 1341, when a flood carved out its harbor and opened it to Arab, Chinese and European merchants. Sites reflecting those influences include Fort Kochi, a settlement with tiled colonial bungalows and diverse houses of worship. Cantilevered Chinese fishing nets, typical of Kochi, have been in use for centuries.</p>', 'National', '3', '1', NULL, '1', '1', '1', 36500, NULL, '2023-07-22 04:35:09'),
(8, 9, 'Hyderabad', 'eduInstitute', 'Sawai Madhopur', NULL, NULL, 'DELHI JAIPUR RANTHAMBORE NATIONAL PARK', 'DELHI JAIPUR RANTHAMBORE NATIONAL PARK', 'DELHI JAIPUR RANTHAMBORE NATIONAL PARK HYDERABAD PRIME MINISTER MUSEUM INDIA GATE RASHTRAPATI BHAWAN KARTAVYA PATH SAWAI MADHOPUR PADAM TALAO RANTHAMBORE FORT CITY PALACE HAWA MAHAL ALBERT HALL MUSEUM BAPU BAZAR AMBER FORT', 'JAIPUR: Jaipur is popularly known as the Pink City of Rajasthan, which is not only Pink but also the most colorful city of India. The city is the mixture and combination of Indian culture and modern experiences\nRANTHAMBORE: Ranthambore is known for its large tiger population. It is bounded to the north by the Banas River and to the south by the Chambal River.', 'ranthambhore-national-park-13jpg-1677488008338336.jpeg', 'Ranthambhore-National-Park_13.jpg', 'itinerary_image_63f9c15f4ed25', 'itinerary_image_63f9c15f4ed22', 6, '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>JAIPUR: </strong>Jaipur is popularly known as the Pink City of Rajasthan, which is not only Pink but also the most colorful city of India. The city is the mixture and combination of Indian culture and modern experiences</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>RANTHAMBORE: </strong>Ranthambore is known for its large tiger population. It is bounded to the north by the Banas River and to the south by the Chambal River.</p>', 'National', '3', '0', '1', NULL, '1', '1', 21500, NULL, '2023-07-21 13:07:26'),
(9, 11, 'Hyderabad', 'eduInstitute', 'Bangaluru', NULL, NULL, 'BANGALORE COORG MYSORE WONDERLA', 'BANGALORE COORG MYSORE WONDERLA', 'BANGALORE COORG MADIKERI MYSORE WONDERLA TIPU SUMMER PALACE Visvesvaraya Science Museum Vidhana Soudha Bull Temple Abbey Falls Madikeri Fort Mysore Palace Brindavan Gardens Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) Museum', 'Bangalore is sometimes referred to as the Silicon Valley of India (or IT capital of India) because of its role as the nation\'s leading information technology (IT) exporter. Indian technological organizations ISRO, Infosys, Wipro and HAL are headquartered in the city.\nThe coffee plantations of Coorg are famous globally and attract many tourists. The remote and less popular waterfalls also make for beautiful photographs and lush natural beauty. These are some of the top reasons to plan a trip to Coorg.\nMysore is noted for its heritage structures and palaces, including the Mysore Palace, and for the festivities that take place during the Dasara festival when the city receives hundreds of thousands of tourists from around the world.\nWonderla is the largest chain of amusement parks in India.', 'wonderla-2jpg-1677491965602260.jpeg', 'Wonderla_2.jpg', 'itinerary_image_63f9ee78ad6d5', 'itinerary_image_63f9ee78ad6d2', 6, '<p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Bangalore </strong>is sometimes referred to as the Silicon Valley of India (or IT capital of India) because of its role as the nation\'s leading information technology (IT) exporter. Indian technological organizations ISRO, Infosys, Wipro and HAL are headquartered in the city.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>The coffee plantations of Coorg</strong> are famous globally and attract many tourists. The remote and less popular waterfalls also make for beautiful photographs and lush natural beauty. These are some of the top reasons to plan a trip to Coorg.</p><p class=\"ql-align-justify\"><strong>Mysore </strong>is noted for its heritage structures and palaces, including the Mysore Palace, and for the festivities that take place during the Dasara festival when the city receives hundreds of thousands of tourists from around the world.</p><p><strong>Wonderla</strong> is the largest chain of amusement parks in India.</p>', 'National', '3', NULL, '1', NULL, '1', '1', 19000, NULL, '2023-07-21 13:50:32'),
